Herbert Menges was appointed an Officer of the Order of the British Empire in 1963 .

Leutnant Helmut Dilthey IC ( 9 February 1894 - 9 July 1918 ) was a German pilot who became a World War I flying ace credited with seven aerial victories .
Wilburn Chandler Hamilton was a veteran of World War II who decided in 1957 to settle on the island of Saipan .

Edwin T. Woodward ( March 8 , 1843 -- February 22 , 1894 ) , was a naval officer during and after the American Civil War .
George Dashiell Bayard ( December 18 , 1835 -- December 14 , 1862 ) was a career soldier in the United States Army and a general in the Union Army in the American Civil War .
The T-26 was the most important tank of the Spanish Civil War and played a significant role during the Battle of Lake Khasan in 1938 as well as in the Winter War in 1939 - -40 .
General Edward Braddock ( January 1695 -- 13 July 1755 ) was a British officer and commander - in - chief for the 13 colonies during the actions at the start of the French and Indian War ( 1754 - -1765 ) which is also known in Europe as the Seven Years ' War ( 1756 - -1763 ) .
Hermann Lichtenberger ( 20 August 1892 -- 15 January 1959 ) was a highly decorated Generalmajor in the Luftwaffe during World War II who commanded the Flak - Brigade IV . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
Max Immelmann ( 21 September 1890 -- 18 June 1916 ) PLM was the first German World War I flying ace .
Sergeant Thomas Frederick Stephenson DCM ( 1894 -- 20 November 1917 ) was a British World War I flying ace credited with five aerial victories .
Arnaldo Mussolini , like his brother Benito Mussolini , took part in World War I , attaining the rank of lieutenant , and in 1919 after the war 's end , he moved to Milan .
Flight Sergeant Frank Sumner , was a British RAF air gunner during World War II and flew combat missions during the Battle of Britain .
Jean Pierre François Bonet , Count of Bonet ( born 8 August 1768 in Alençon ; † 23 November 1857 Alençon ) was a French military commander during the French Revolutionary Wars and Napoleonic Wars .
Wing Commander Douglas Arthur Davies DFC ( 12 January 1896 -- 1992 ) was an officer of the British Royal Air Force , who was credited with 10 aerial victories in World War I , and also served during World War II .

Lieutenant James Alfred Keating was a World War I flying ace credited with six aerial victories , including four triumphs during a running battle on 9 August 1918 .
Philippe de Culant ( 1413 -- December 1454 ) was a French nobleman and soldier of the Hundred Years ' War .
John Lorimer Worden ( March 12 , 1818 -- October 19 , 1897 ) was a U.S. Navy officer in the American Civil War , who took part in the Battle of Hampton Roads , the first - ever engagement between ironclad steamships at Hampton Roads , Virginia , on 9 March 1862 .
Moses Orr ( 1847 -- May 10 , 1897 ) was an Irish - born soldier in the U.S. Army who served with the 1st U.S. Cavalry during the Apache Wars .
Robert Strahan ( born 21 March 1838 ) was an American sailor who received the Medal of Honor for valor in action during the American Civil War .
Karl - Wilhelm von Schlieben ( 30 October 1894 -- 18 June 1964 ) was a German officer in World War I and World War II .

Atilla Sertel ( born 23 July 1956 ) is a Turkish politician and journalist from the Republican People 's Party ( CHP ) who has served as a Member of Parliament for İzmir 's second electoral district since the November 2015 general election .
Helen Masters ( born 10 April 1963 ) is an English actress who has appeared on stage , film and TV .

Sohail Tanvir ( Urdu : سہیل تنویر , born 12 December 1984 in Rawalpindi , Punjab ) is a Pakistani cricketer , who has gained repute for his unorthodox left arm bowling action and particularly for the success it has gained him in the Twenty20 format of the game .

Presley Thornton ( 1721 - December 8 , 1769 ) was a planter and public official in Colonial Virginia .
Edward Finney ( 1903 - -1983 ) was an American film producer and director .
Torger Reve ( born 31 March 1949 ) is a Norwegian economist , Professor at the BI Norwegian Business School and rector of the BI from 1997 to 2005 , particularly known for his work on marketing , distribution channels and interorganizational relations .
Susan Clough ( born 1945 ) was the personal executive secretary to President Jimmy Carter .
Erik Voake is an American filmmaker and photographer born in Yorba Linda , California in 1973 .
Norbert Meier ( born 20 September 1958 ) is a German former football player and current manager of Arminia Bielefeld .
Grzegorz Adam Urbanowski ( born 24 December 1959 in Pultusk ) , Polish ultramarathon racewalker .
Ge Guangrui ( 葛光锐 , Shanghai , 1929 ) is a Chinese composer .
Nina Bari was born in Russia on 19 November 1901 , the daughter of Olga and Karl Adolfovich Bari , a physician .
Edwina Hayes ( born 6 June 1973 , in Dublin , Ireland ) is an Irish born English singer - songwriter .
Hrvoje Šarinić ( pronounced ( xr̩̂ʋoje ʃǎrinit͡ɕ ) ; born 17 February 1935 ) is a former Croatian politician .
Andy Dixon ( born 25 August 1979 ) is a Canadian artist and musician , who gained notoriety as a member of the North Vancouver punk rock band d.b.s .
Esther Ibanga ( born 31 March 1961 ) is a Nigerian pastor and founder of the `` Women Without Walls Initiative '' .
Attila Csihar ( Hungarian : ( ˈɒtilːɒ ˈt͡ʃihɒr ) ; born 29 March 1971 ) , also sometimes known as Void , is a Hungarian black metal vocalist , best known for his vocal work on Mayhem 's De Mysteriis Dom Sathanas album .
Luján Fernández ( born 1985 ) is a former Argentine model , perhaps best known for her three - year run in the Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue .
Merle Terlesky ( born 1965 ) is a Canadian conservative activist , originally from Kamloops , British Columbia .

Wu Yen - hsia or Wu Yanxia ( 1930 - -2001 ) was a Chinese t'ai chi ch'uan teacher of Manchu ancestry .
Ulysses Grant Groff ( 29 October 1865 -- 15 October 1950 ) was a large landowner and philanthropist noted for substantial donations to the City of Amherst , Massachusetts and to Amherst College .
Jang Su - jeong ( Korean : 장수정 hanja : 張修貞 ; born 13 March 1995 in Busan ) is a South Korean tennis player .

Duccia Camiciotti ( 19 March 1928 -- 7 July 2014 ) was an Italian poet , writer and essayist .
Christopher Gordon Horsfall Simon JP ( 14 November 1914 -- 20 February 2002 ) , known as C. G. H. Simon , was a British General Commissioner of Income Tax .
Bill Townsend ( born 1964 ) is an entrepreneur who helped build several global companies , most notably search engine Lycos , social networking pioneer sixdegrees.com , whose intellectual property formed the basis of LinkedIn , GeoCities ( sold to Yahoo ! ) and Deja.com ( sold to Google and ebay ) .
Packard Jennings is an American artist ( b. 1970 ) who appropriates pop culture symbols and references to create new meaning using a variety of media including printmaking , sculpture , animation , video , and pamphleteering .
Keshavdas Mishra ( 1555 -- 1617 ) , usually known by the mononym Keshavdas or Keshavadasa , was a Sanskrit scholar and Hindi poet , best known for his Rasik Priya , a pioneering work of the riti kaal ( procedure period ) of Hindi literature .
Sean Landless ( born 1986 ) is an English actor who plays the lead role in the 2001 film , Gabriel & Me .
Damian Bourke ( born 19 January 1965 ) is a former Australian rules footballer for Australian Football League ( AFL ) clubs Geelong during the 1980s and Brisbane in the early 1990s .
Ehud Yatom ( Hebrew : אהוד יתום‎ , born 26 September 1948 ) is an Israeli former Shin Bet agent and politician who briefly served as a member of the Knesset for Likud from 2003 until 2006 .
Dan Empfield ( born 1957 ) is an entrepreneur in the world of multisport , inventor of the triathlon wetsuit in 1987 , and the triathlon - specific racing bike in 1989 .
Rifat Artikov ( born 24 January 1983 , in Tashkent Region ) is an Uzbek decathlete .

The Gruen Transfer is an Australian television program focusing on advertising , which debuted on ABC1 on 28 May 2008 and has run for four seasons .
The Gene Autry Show is an American western / cowboy television series which aired for 91 episodes on CBS from July 23 , 1950 until August 7 , 1956 , originally sponsored by Wrigley 's Doublemint chewing gum .
Dagsrevyen ( English : The Daily Review ) is the daily evening news programme for the Norwegian television channel NRK1 , the main channel of the Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation ( NRK ) , broadcast at 19:00 .
Gudtaym ( Filipinization of the phrase `` good time '' ) is a Friday night variety show on ABS - CBN .
It Could Happen Tomorrow is a television series that premiered on January 15 , 2006 on The Weather Channel .
Chandrakant Chiplunkar Seedi Bambawala was an Indian situational comedy television series that aired on SAB TV .
The Problem Solverz is an American animated television series created by Ben Jones , a member of the art collective Paper Rad , for Cartoon Network .
Rosie and Jim ( sometimes written as Rosie & Jim ) is a British children 's television programme produced by Ragdoll Productions and aired on ITV from 3 September 1990 to 31 March 2000 , and on PBS from 5 September 1992 to 25 May 2001 .
Barney Blake , Police Reporter is an American crime drama that aired live on NBC from April 22 , 1948 to July 8 , 1948 .
Real People is an NBC reality television series that aired from 1979 to 1984 , on Wednesday and then Sunday nights .
The Three Friends and Jerry is a Swedish animated television series which aired in the United States on Fox Family , Nickelodeon in the UK and Latin America , TG4 in Ireland and Fox Kids in Spain .
Tales of Wells Fargo is an American Western television series starring Dale Robertson that ran from 1957 to 1962 on NBC .
The Nightlife is a dance - themed television series originally airing on TeenNick .
Wolf Lake is an American television series that originally aired on CBS .
Cade 's County is a modern - day Western / crime drama which aired on CBS during the 1971 - -1972 television season .
Da Vinci 's Inquest is a Canadian dramatic television series that aired on CBC Television from 1998 to 2005 .
Dog Bites Man was a partially improvised comedy television show on Comedy Central that aired in summer 2006 .
Good Time Harry is an American sitcom that aired on NBC from July 19 , 1980 to September 13 , 1980 .
The George Wendt Show is an American television sitcom that aired on CBS from March 8 , to April 12 , 1995 .
Imortal ( lit . Immortal ) is a Philippine television drama produced by ABS - CBN .
Tittybangbang is a female - led television sketch comedy , performed by Lucy Montgomery and Debbie Chazen , which ran between 2005 and 2007 on BBC Three .
The Karen Dunbar Show was a television comedy sketch show that aired on BBC One Scotland , starring the popular Scottish comedian Karen Dunbar ( of Chewin ' the Fat fame ) .
RIS Delitti Imperfetti is an Italian television series , created in 2004 by Daniele Cesarano , Barbara Petronio and Leonardo Valenti , broadcast since January 2005 on Canale 5 .
Dastardly and Muttley in Their Flying Machines is a cartoon produced by Hanna - Barbera Productions for CBS .
Quebec in English is a Canadian television miniseries which aired on CBC Television in 1965 .
Early Edition is an American television drama series that aired on CBS broadcast network from September 28 , 1996 to May 27 , 2000 .
Baba 's Cross Connection is an Indian television show featuring rapper Baba Sehgal on Imagine Showbiz .
Good Luck Charlie , It 's Christmas ! ( also known as Good Luck Charlie : The Road Trip Movie in the United Kingdom and Ireland ) is a 2011 Christmas film based on the Disney Channel Original Series Good Luck Charlie .
Hatching Pete is a 2009 Disney Channel Original Movie which first aired on April 24 , 2009 on Disney Channel UK and later Disney Channel and Family .
NBA Shootaround is a pregame show for ESPN 's coverage of the National Basketball Association ( NBA ) .
Dharti Ka Veer Yodha Prithviraj Chauhan Produced by Sagar Pictures ( English : Prithviraj Chauhan , the Brave Warrior of the Land ) is an Indian historical drama broadcast on Star Plus .
Falcon Crest is an American prime time television soap opera that aired for nine seasons on CBS from December 4 , 1981 to May 17 , 1990 .
On Camera was a Canadian dramatic anthology television series which aired on CBC Television from 1954 to 1958 .
Paalkhi is a Hindi language Indian drama television series which premiered on 13 June 2005 on Zee TV .
Camp Cucamonga ( also titled : How I Spent My Summer and Lights Out ) is a made - for - television movie that was first aired on NBC on September 23 , 1990 .
The Kraft Suspense Theatre is an American anthology series that was produced and broadcast from 1963 to 1965 on NBC .
Santo Bugito is a 1995 animated cartoon series produced and developed by Klasky - Csupo for CBS and created by Arlene Klasky .
Goodsports is an Australian children 's television series , produced by WIN Television in Hobart , Tasmania .
Vidas prestadas is a 2000 telenovela produced by Venevisión International and Iguana Producciones .
Like Family is an American sitcom that aired on The WB in 2003 .
PoliticsNation with Al Sharpton is a one - hour political talk show broadcast on MSNBC , hosted by Al Sharpton .
Stolen Voices , Buried Secrets is an American true crime television series on the Investigation Discovery Network .
Sanford and Son is an American sitcom , that ran on the NBC television network from January 14 , 1972 to March 25 , 1977 .
King Arthur 's Disasters is a British animated series which first aired on CITV .
Chico and the Man is an American sitcom which ran on NBC for four seasons , from September 13 , 1974 , to July 21 , 1978 .
Andando nas Nuvens ( English : Walking on Clouds ) is a Brazilian telenovela produced and broadcast by Rede Globo originally ran from March 22 to November 5 , 1999 for 197 episodes .
The 92 KQRS Morning Show ( also known as the KQ Morning Crew ) is a popular , long - running radio morning show originating from KQRS - FM in Minneapolis , Minnesota .
Coenophlebia is a genus of neotropical charaxine butterflies in the family Nymphalidae , native to Colombia , Peru , Brazil , Bolivia and Ecuador .
The Tibetan babax ( Babax koslowi ) is a species of bird in the Leiothrichidae family .
Styloniscus is a genus of woodlice in the family Styloniscidae .
Diopatra is a genus of polychaete worms in the family Onuphidae .
Chironominae is a subfamily of midges in the non - biting midge family ( Chironomidae ) .
The Bolivian big - eared mouse ( Auliscomys boliviensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Heliscomyidae is a member of the clade Geomyoidea , a group of rodents that also includes the families †Eomyidae , †Florentiamyidae , Heteromyidae , and Geomyidae .
Gonyleptoidea is the most diverse superfamily of the Grassatores .
Pseudotolithus is a genus of croaker or bar , ray - finned fish in the family Sciaenidae .
Metarhizium is a genus of entomopathogenic fungi in the Clavicipitaceae family .
The New Zealand rough skate , Dipturus nasutus , is a skate of the genus Dipturus , found around New Zealand at depths of between 10 and 1,500 m. Their length is up to 1 m.
Apiopetalum is a genus of plant of family Apiaceae , comprising 2 species .
The Sardinian meadow brown ( Maniola nurag ) is a butterfly belonging to the Nymphalidae family .
The Russian wheat aphid ( Diuraphis noxia ) is an aphid that can cause significant losses in cereal crops .
Acamptocladius is a genus of non - biting midges in the subfamily Orthocladiinae of the bloodworm family Chironomidae .
Neolepetopsoidea was synonymized with Lottioidea so Daminilidae was moved to superfamily Lottioidea in World Register of Marine Species .
Christine 's margareta rat ( Margaretamys christinae ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Orthops is a genus of Miridae in the subfamily Mirinae .
The Mount Coke false shieldback ( Acilacris furcatus ) is a tettigoniid orthopteran that is endemic to a single small locality in Eastern Cape Province , South Africa .
The Hawaiian rail ( Porzana sandwichensis ) , Hawaiian spotted rail , or Hawaiian crake was a somewhat enigmatic species of diminutive rail that lived on Big Island of Hawaiʻi , but is now extinct .
Marionia is a genus of sea slugs , specifically dendronotid nudibranchs , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Tritoniidae .
Bosistoa is a genus of Australian plants with 6 species in the family Rutaceae .
Winter savory ( Satureja montana ) is a perennial herb in the family Lamiaceae , native to warm temperate regions of southern Europe and Mediterranean .
The Madang big - eyed tree frog , Nyctimystes disruptus , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family , endemic to Papua New Guinea .
Beringius is a genus of large sea snails or true whelks , a marine gastropod molluscs in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
The Peru poison frog ( also Peruvian poison frog or Peruvian poison - arrow frog ; Ameerega petersi ) is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family It is found in eastern Peru ( Ucayali River and Huallaga River basins ) and western Brazil ( Acre state ) .
The Chacoan naked - tailed armadillo ( Cabassous chacoensis ) is a species of South American armadillo .
Lobulia is a genus of skinks in the subfamily Lygosominae .
Tetracentrum is a genus of fish in the family Ambassidae , the Asiatic glassfishes .
Cetotherium ( `` whale beast '' ) is a genus of cetaceans from the family Cetotheriidae .
Hypisodus is an extinct genus belonging to the family Hypertragulidae , within the order Artiodactyla , endemic to North America during the Eocene through Oligocene , living 37.2 - -26.3 Ma , existing for approximately 10.9 million years .
The Brazilian large - eyed stingray , Dasyatis marianae , is a species of stingray in the family Dasyatidae .
The Red Hills salamander ( Phaeognathus hubrichti ) is a fairly large , terrestrial salamander growing to about 255 millimetres ( 10.0 in ) .
The East African highland shrew ( Crocidura allex ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
The Australian wood frog ( Hylarana daemeli ) , locally simply known as the wood frog , is the only species from the family Ranidae found in Australia .
Waller 's starling ( Onychognathus walleri ) is a species of starling in the family Sturnidae .
The Mohave ground squirrel ( Xerospermophilus mohavensis ) is a species of ground squirrel found only in the Mojave Desert in California .
Onykia is a genus of squids in the family Onychoteuthidae .
Gabb 's snail also known as the San Clemente Island snail , scientific name Micrarionta gabbii , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helminthoglyptidae .
Durotrigensia is a genus of ammonites ( Ammonitida ) in the perisphinctoid family Parkinsoniidae .
The Laysan rail or Laysan crake ( Porzana palmeri ) was a flightless bird endemic to the Northwest Hawaiian Island of Laysan .
The Rouget 's rail ( Rougetius rougetii ) is a species of bird in the family Rallidae .
With 622 valid species assigned by 1987 to the subtribe Paederina ( Paederus and its close allies ) , and with all but 148 within Paederus itself , the genus is large .
Kutchicetus ( `` Kutch whale '' ) is an extinct genus of early whale of the family Remingtonocetidae that lived during Early - Middle Eocene ( Lutetian and Ypresian ) in what is now the coastal border of Pakistan and India ( 23.7 ° N 68.7 ° E , paleocoordinates 6.0 ° N 61.8 ° E ) .
The Mascarene petrel ( Pseudobulweria aterrima ) is a medium - sized , dark gadfly petrel .
Momordica is a genus of about 60 species of annual or perennial climbers herbaceous or rarely small shrubs belonging to the family Cucurbitaceae , natives of tropical and subtropical Africa and Asia and Australia .
Finsch 's bulbul ( Alophoixus finschii ) is a species of songbird in the Pycnonotidae family .
The Appalachian monkey - face pearly mussel or Appalachian monkeyface , scientific name Quadrula sparsa , is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Pseudochama is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Chamidae .
Sphaeropsidales is an order of Coelomycetes fungi .
The Izu catshark ( Scyliorhinus tokubee ) is a species of catshark , family Scyliorhinidae , found only in the waters around Japan , at depths down to 100 m. It can grow up to a length of 41 cm .
Ginglymostoma unami , also known as the Pacific nurse shark is a nurse sharks of the family Ginglymostomatidae .
Oxycerites is an extinct ammonoid cephalopod belonging to the haploceratacean family , Oppeliidae , that lived during the Middle Jurassic .
Tantulocarida is a highly specialised group of parasitic crustaceans that consists of about 33 species , treated as a subclass of the class Maxillopoda ( copepods and barnacles ) .
Pseudococcus is a genus of unarmoured scale insects in the family Pseudococcidae , the mealy bugs .
The Oriental skylark ( Alauda gulgula ) , also known as the Oriental lark or small skylark , is a species of skylark found on the Indian Subcontinent and Southeast Asia .
Enterogona is an order of tunicates in the class Ascidiacea .
Bengalia is a genus of blow flies in the family Calliphoridae with one authority considering the genus to belong to a separate family Bengaliidae .
Chaetothyriomycetidae is a subclass of ascomycetes within the class Eurotiomycetes .
Aspidoras is easily distinguished from the other genera of the subfamily Corydoradinae by the presence of a supraoccipital fontanel ; this character is an autapomorphy for the genus .
Leptotrombidium ( /ˌlɛptoʊtrɒmˈbɪdiəm/ ) is a genus of mites in the family Trombiculidae , that are able to infect humans with scrub typhus ( Orientia tsutsugamushi infection ) through their bite .
Sitona is a large genus of weevils in the family Curculionidae native to the Nearctic and Palaearctic regions .
The Bougainville monkey - faced bat ( Pteralopex anceps ) is a megabat found only on islands of Bougainville and Choiseul in Melanesia .
Swainson 's thrush ( Catharus ustulatus ) , also called olive - backed thrush , is a medium - sized thrush .
Purgatorius is the genus of the four extinct species believed to be the earliest example of a primate or a proto - primate , a primatomorph precursor to the Plesiadapiformes , dating to as old as 66 million years ago .
Pterocephalus is a genus in the Caprifoliaceae family of herbs and shrubs , comprising 25 species ranging from the Mediterranean , to central Asia , the Himalayas , western China , and tropical Africa .
The Guianan cock - of - the - rock ( Rupicola rupicola ) is a species of South American passerine .
Marburg marburgvirus is a virological taxon ( i.e. a man - made concept ) included in the genus Marburgvirus , family Filoviridae , order Mononegavirales .
The South Island oystercatcher or South Island pied oystercatcher ( Haematopus finschi ) is one of the two common oystercatchers found in New Zealand .
The Mozambique thicket rat ( Grammomys cometes ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
†Pseudohelenoconcha was a genus of air - breathing land snails , shell - less terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Endodontidae .
Sampson 's naiad , Sampson 's pearly mussel , Sampson 's riffleshell , or wabash riffleshell , scientific name Epioblasma sampsonii , was a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
The Neotropical green anole ( Anolis biporcatus ) is a species of Anolis lizard , native to Central America and northern South America , from Mexico to Ecuador and Venezuela .
Slowinski 's corn snake ( Pantherophis slowinskii ) is a species of nonvenomous snake indigenous to Arkansas .
The Greater Mindanao shrew ( Crocidura grandis ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Okenia is a genus of colorful sea slugs , specifically of dorid nudibranchs , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Goniodorididae .
The Cuban evening bat ( Nycticeius cubanus ) is a species of bat in the vesper bat family , Vespertilionidae , that is endemic to western Cuba .
Genotina is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Mangeliidae ,
Centrophorus seychellorum or Seychelles gulper shark , is a species of fish in the Centrophoridae family found in Alphonse island in Seychelles .
Chlamydogobius micropterus , the Elizabeth Springs goby , is a species of goby endemic to Queensland , Australia where it occurs in shallow , marshy pools .
Muscicapa is a genus of passerine birds belonging to the Old World flycatcher family Muscicapidae , and therein to the typical flycatchers of subfamily Muscicapinae .
Dimitshydrus typhlops is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Dimitshydrus .
Chamaesium is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae , with 5 to 8 species .
The Amphinectidae are a spider family with about 180 described species in 35 genera .
They are the namesake family of the huge and little - studied superfamily Gelechioidea , and the Gelechiidae 's relationships with and delimitation against their relatives have been subject to considerable dispute .
Hegetotheria is a suborder of the extinct mammalian order Notoungulata and includes two families , Archaeohyracidae and Hegetotheriidae .
Viverravidae is an extinct family within the superfamily Miacoidea .
Galerella is a genus of the mongoose family ( Herpestidae ) native to Africa and commonly called the slender mongooses .
Pongo hooijeri is an extinct species of orangutan from the Pleistocene of Vietnam .
Cycadidae is a subclass of Equisetopsida in the sense used by Mark W. Chase and James L. Reveal in their 2009 article `` A phylogenetic classification of the land plants to accompany APG III . '' This subclass comprises the cycads , which include the two families Cycadaceae and Zamiaceae .
Stegocephalidae is a little - studied family of amphipods belonging to the suborder Gammaridea .
Apistobuthus is a genus of scorpions in the family Buthidae .
Hippocastanoideae is a subfamily of flowering plants in the soapberry family , Sapindaceae .
The Kanab ambersnail , scientific name Oxyloma haydeni kanabense or Oxyloma kanabense , is a critically endangered subspecies or species of small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Succineidae , the amber snails .
The Mindoro hornbill ( Penelopides mindorensis ) is a species of hornbill in the Bucerotidae family .
Haptoderidius debeckeri is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Haptoderidius .
Arrhoges is a monospecific genus of medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Aporrhaidae and the superfamily Stromboidea .
The Montagu 's harrier ( Circus pygargus ) is a migratory bird of prey of the harrier family .
Aachenosaurus is a dubious genus of prehistoric plant .
The California quail ( Callipepla californica ) , also known as the California valley quail or valley quail , is a small ground - dwelling bird in the New World quail family .
The Naomi 's forest frog ( Platymantis naomii ) is a species of frog in the Ceratobatrachidae family .
Philomma was a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , it is now considered a synonym of Derrima .
The Greek lamprey ( Eudontomyzon hellenicus ) ( also known as the Greek brook lamprey ) is a species of jawless fish in the Petromyzontidae family .
`` We assign Hainina to the Kogaionidae ( superfamily incertae sedis ) ; it differs from Kogaionon in having ornamented enamel , while the enamel is smooth in Kogaionon , '' ( Kielan - Jaworowska & Hurum , 2001 , p.409 ) .
Tasmanida norfolkae is a species of squat lobster in a monotypic genus in the family Munididae .
The Oxypeltidae are a small family belonging to the superfamily Chrysomeloidea , widespread in the Andean region of Chile and Argentina .

Terraconia is a genus of very small freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrobiidae .
Devil 's club or devil 's walking stick ( Oplopanax horridus , Araliaceae ; syn . Echinopanax horridus , Fatsia horrida ) is a large understory shrub endemic to the arboreal rainforests of the pacific northwest , but also disjunct on islands in Lake Superior .
Highback chub ( Hybopsis hypsinotus ) is a species of freshwater fish in the carp family ( Cyprinidae ) .
Vaillant 's frog ( Rana vaillanti ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family found in Belize , Colombia , Costa Rica , Ecuador , Guatemala , Honduras , Mexico , Nicaragua , and Panama .
The Snow Mountains quail ( Anurophasis monorthonyx ) , also known as the Snow Mountain quail , is a large , approximately 28 cm ( 11 in ) long , dark brown quail of Alpine grasslands .
Cereeae are a tribe of cactus belonging to the Cactoideae subfamily .
Humerana is a genus of frogs in the Ranidae family from southern and southeastern Asia .
Lithocarpus is a genus in the beech family Fagaceae , differing from Quercus in the erect male spikes .
Katinka 's shrew ( Crocidura katinka ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
The Petit 's cuckooshrike ( Campephaga petiti ) is a species of bird in the Campephagidae family .
Plicatodus is a prehistoric shark in the family Xenacanthidae , that existed during the lower Permian in what is now Germany .
The Bonin wood pigeon ( Columba versicolor ) was a pigeon endemic to Nakodo - jima and Chichi - jima in the Ogasawara Islands , south of Japan .
Arionidae , common name the `` roundback slugs '' or `` round back slugs '' are a taxonomic family of air - breathing land slugs , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Arionoidea .
Ypresiomyrma is an extinct genus of ants in the subfamily Myrmeciinae that was described in 2006 .
Camissoniopsis is a plant genus in the evening primrose family Onagraceae .
Synagelides is a genus of Asian spiders of the Salticidae family ( jumping spiders ) .
Pterostillichus caecus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Pterostillichus .
Phylloglossum , a genus in the clubmoss family Huperziaceae , is a small plant superficially resembling a tiny grass plant , growing with a rosette of slender leaves 2 - 5 cm long from an underground bulb - like root .
The Meso - American slider ( Trachemys venusta ) is a species of turtle belonging to the family Emydidae with a distribution from Mexico to Colombia .
Heteralepas is a genus of goose barnacles in the family Heteralepadidae .
Pellona is a genus of ray - finned fishes in the Pristigasteridae family .
Fallotaspidella is a derived member of the superfamily `` Fallotaspidoidea '' .
The Mwanza flat - headed rock agama ( Agama mwanzae ) or the Spider - Man agama , because of its coloration , is a lizard in the family Agamidae , found in Tanzania , Rwanda , and Kenya .
Species in the genus Phelsuma are commonly referred to as day geckos .
Koumansetta hectori , Hector 's goby , is a species of goby native to the Indian Ocean ( including the Red Sea ) to the islands of Micronesia in the western Pacific Ocean .
Orobanchaceae , the broomrapes , is a family of parasitic plants of the order Lamiales , with about 90 genera and more than 2000 species .
Argestina is a butterfly genus of the Satyrinae .
Exellodendron is a genus of plant in the family Chrysobalanaceae described as a genus in 1972 .
The Jonah crab ( Cancer borealis ) is a marine brachyuran crab that inhabits waters along the east coast of North America from Newfoundland to Florida .
Paleoboa is an extinct genus of snake from the Eocene of Germany .
Chromoeme angustissima is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Chromoeme .
The Persian vole ( Microtus irani ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Nardoa is a genus of sea star of the family Ophidiasteridae .
The Mycetopodidae are a family of freshwater pearly mussels in the order Unionoida restricted to South America .
The Japanese sleeper ray ( Narke japonica ) is a species of electric ray in the family Narkidae .
Italodytes stammeri is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Italodytes .
Panthera onca augusta , commonly known as the Pleistocene North American jaguar , is an extinct subspecies of the jaguar that was endemic to North and South America during the Pleistocene epoch ( 1.8 mya--11,000 years ago ) .
The Campbell teal or Campbell Island teal ( Anas nesiotis ) is a small , flightless , nocturnal species of dabbling duck of the genus Anas endemic to the Campbell Island group of New Zealand .
The Rudd 's mole - rat ( Tachyoryctes ruddi ) is a species of rodents in the family Spalacidae .
Ecsenius is a large genus of fish in the Blenniidae family .
Dryoctenes scrupulosus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Dryoctenes .
Amniscites pictipes is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Amniscites .
Zythiostroma is a genus of canker fungus in the Nectriaceae family .
Campylosiphon is a genus of flowering plants in the Burmanniaceae , first described as a genus in 1882 .
Equisetidae is a subclass of Equisetopsida in the sense used by Mark W. Chase and James L. Reveal in their 2009 article `` A phylogenetic classification of the land plants to accompany APG III . '' This subclass comprises the group commonly known as horsetails .
Haminoea is a genus of medium - sized sea snails or bubble snails , marine opisthobranch gastropod molluscs in the family Haminoeidae , the haminoea bubble snails , part of the clade Cephalaspidea , the headshield slugs and bubble snails .
Trichonis blenny , Salaria economidisi , is a species of fish in the Blenniidae family .
Typhlocaris is a genus of blind cave - dwelling shrimp , placed in its own family , Typhlocarididae .
Cuckoo bumblebees are members of the subgenus Psithyrus in the bumblebee genus Bombus .
Eriodictyon is a genus of plants within the Hydrophylloideae subfamily of the Boraginaceae family .
The Táchira antpitta ( Grallaria chthonia ) is a cryptical bird species .
Gynocladius is a parthenogenetic genus in the subfamily Orthocladiinae ( Chironomidae ) .
Silvacola is an extinct genus of hedgehog of the family Erinaceidae , which lived in North America during the Eocene , 50 million years ago .
Xibalbanus tulumensis ( previously Speleonectes tulumensis -- Speleonectes = ' cave swimmer ' ; tulumensis = ' occurring at Tulum ' -- Xibalbanus = ' from Xibalba ' ) is a venomous , hermaphroditic crustacean found in anchialine caves on the Yucatán Peninsula in the Caribbean Sea .
The Güldenstädt 's redstart ( Phoenicurus erythrogastrus ) also sometimes called the white - winged redstart , is a species of bird in the genus Phoenicurus , family Muscicapidae .
Synchiropus stellatus , commonly known as the Starry dragonet , is a species of dragonet native to the Indian Ocean where it is found at depths of around 40 metres ( 130 ft ) .
Gray 's stream frog ( Strongylopus grayii ) is a fairly small species of frog in the family Pyxicephalidae .
Oxycomanthus is a genus of crinoids belonging to the family Comasteridae .
Hydaticus is a genus of predatory water beetle belonging to the family Dytiscidae , native to the Palearctic ( including Europe ) , the Afro - tropical region , the Near East , the Nearctic and North Africa .
Parmelinae is a genus of lichen belonging to the family Parmeliaceae .
Belone belone ( Linnaeus , 1761 ) ( Garfish ) Belone svetovidovi Collette & Parin , 1970 ( Short - beaked garfish )
Macadamia is a genus of four species of trees indigenous to Australia and constituting part of the plant family Proteaceae .
Allen 's cotton rat ( Sigmodon alleni ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Bactericera is a psyllid bug genus in the family Triozidae .
Helicodiscidae is a family of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrialpulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Punctoidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
The Manus boobook ( Ninox meeki ) is a small owl .
The German cockroach ( Blattella germanica ) is a small species of cockroach , typically about 1.1 to 1.6 cm ( 0.43 to 0.63 in ) long .
The genus Janetaescincus is usually placed in the subfamily Scincinae , which seems to be paraphyletic however .
The Olympic shrew ( Sorex rohweri ) is a rare species of shrew that lives in only 13 spots in northwest Washington State and , a recent discovery , in Burns Bog , located in Delta , BC . Not much is known about this species .

The Socotra sunbird ( Chalcomitra balfouri ) is a species of bird in the Nectariniidae family .
Nymphoides , or floatingheart , is a genus of aquatic flowering plants in the family Menyanthaceae .
Pultenaea belongs to the tribe Mirbelieae , sister to tribe Bossiaeeae ; family Fabaceae - Faboideae Pultenaea possibly not monophyletic , and is poorly resolved .
The Thai whiting , Sillago intermedius , is a species of coastal marine fish of the smelt - whiting family Sillaginidae .
Batrachuperus is a genus of salamander in the Hynobiidae family found in western China and adjacent Myanmar .
Carinariidae , known by the common name `` heteropods '' like their relatives in the Pterotracheoidea , is a taxonomic family of swimming or floating sea snails , pelagic marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Syndiclis is a genus of plant in Lauraceae family , In East and South East Asia , From India and China to Indonesia with 12 species known .
The Rockefeller 's sunbird ( Cinnyris rockefelleri ) is a species of bird in the Nectariniidae family .
Biffarius is a genus of ghost shrimp in the family Callianassidae , containing species formerly included in the genus Callianassa .
The Australian pelican ( Pelecanus conspicillatus ) is a large waterbird of the family Pelecanidae , widespread on the inland and coastal waters of Australia and New Guinea , also in Fiji , parts of Indonesia and as a vagrant in New Zealand .
Borogovia was assigned by Osmólska to the Troodontidae in 1987 .
Megalocytivirus is one of five genera of viruses within the family Iridoviridae and one of three genera within this family which infect teleost fishes , along with Lymphocystivirus and Ranavirus .
The Layard 's warbler or Layard 's tit - babbler ( Sylvia layardi ) is a species of Old World warbler in the Sylviidae family .
Senticaudata is one of the four suborders of the crustacean order Amphipoda ( aka scuds , sideswimmers ) .
Spirillum is a genus of Gram - negative bacteria within family Spirillaceae .
Rhabdastrella is a genus of marine sponges belonging to the family of Ancorinidae .
Neomallocera opulenta is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Neomallocera .
Premnoplex is the genus of typical barbtails , birds in the family Furnariidae .
The Tahiti crake ( Porzana nigra ) , also known as Miller 's rail , was a species of bird in the family Rallidae .
The Chinese mystery snail , black snail , or trapdoor snail , scientific name Bellamya chinensis , synonym Cipangopaludina chinensis , is a large freshwater snail with gills and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Viviparidae .
South Island telegraph frog ( Eleutherodactylus audanti ) is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to Hispaniola .
Amorphoscelididae is a family of mantises consisting of 16 genera in the order Mantodea .
The African forest turtle ( Pelusios gabonensis ) is a species of turtle in the family Pelomedusidae .
The Diestoceratidae comprises a family in the nautiloid cephalopod order Oncocerida with compressed , straight to faintly endogastic breviconic shells with a marginal siphuncle that contains discrete , irregular actinosphonate deposits .
The Indian hedgehog ( Paraechinus micropus ) is a species of hedgehog native to India and Pakistan .

Laufeia is a spider genus of the Salticidae family ( jumping spiders ) with Asian distribution , where they are found on shrubs and other plants .
Scaloposauridae is no longer recognized as a valid group , and Scalopocephalus is now classified as a basal member of Baurioidea .
Coscinodiscaceae is a diatom family in the order Coscinodiscales .
Peringia ulvae seems to prefer more exposed localities with less vegetation than Hydrobia ventrosa and Hydrobia neglecta .
Blastozoa is a subphylum of extinct animals belonging to Phylum Echinodermata .
Entoconcha is a genus of very small parasitic sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Eulimidae .
Diplolaemus is a genus of lizards in the family Leiosauridae , endemic to southern South America .
Stylissa is a genus of sponges from Dictyonellidae family .
Caerostris is a genus of spiders in the Araneidae family .
Trochonematidae is an extinct taxonomic family of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Trochonematoidea .
Iuati spinithorax is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Iuati .
Cananeuretus is an extinct genus of ant in the Formicidae subfamily Aneuretinae , and is one of two Cretaceous genera of the subfamily .
Watts 's spiny rat ( Maxomys wattsi ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Western blacknose dace ( Rhinichthys obtusus ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Rhinichthys .
Hypoplectrus indigo , also known as the indigo hamlet , is a species of Hamlet from the Western Central Atlantic .
The Indian crested porcupine ( Hystrix indica ) , or Indian porcupine , is a large species of Hystricomorph rodent ( order Rodentia ) belonging to the Old World porcupine family , Hystricidae .
The Oktedi rainbowfish ( Melanotaenia oktediensis ) is a species of fish in the Melanotaeniidae family .
The East African little collared fruit bat ( Myonycteris relicta ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .

Ariunculus is a genus of air - breathing land slugs in the family Arionidae , the roundback slugs .
The Vogelkop scrubwren ( Sericornis rufescens ) is a bird species .
Gigartinales is a red algae order in the class Florideophyceae .
Chelonariidae is a family of beetles in the superfamily Byrrhoidea .
The genus Pelecinus is the only living member of the family Pelecinidae ( there are also two fossil genera ) , and contains only three species , restricted to the New World .
The leaves of Drepanophycus and Baragwanathia are therefore by definition true microphylls , while those of Asteroxylon are not ; see Drepanophycales for more details .
The Caspian tern ( Hydroprogne caspia , formerly Sterna caspia ) is a species of tern , with a subcosmopolitan but scattered distribution .
The Egyptian vulture ( Neophron percnopterus ) , also called the white scavenger vulture or pharaoh 's chicken , is a small Old World vulture and the only member of the genus Neophron .
Vachellia cornigera , commonly known as Bullhorn Acacia ( family Fabaceae ) , is a swollen - thorn tree native to Mexico and Central America .
Genisteae is a tribe of trees , shrubs and herbaceous plants in the subfamily Faboideae of the legume family Fabaceae .
The Mexican wolf ( Canis lupus baileyi ) , also known as the lobo , is a subspecies of gray wolf once native to southeastern Arizona , southern New Mexico , western Texas and northern Mexico .
Oligoria is a genus of skippers in the Hesperiidae family .
Pemberton 's deer mouse ( Peromyscus pembertoni ) lived on San Pedro Nolasco Island ( 27.96749 ° N 111.37845 ° W ) in the Gulf of California .
The Gran Canaria giant lizard ( Gallotia stehlini ) is a species of lizard in the Lacertidae family that grows to lengths up to 80 cm . It is endemic to Gran Canaria in the Canary Islands of Spain .
Hump - winged grigs are insects belonging to the North American genus Cyphoderris , in the family Prophalangopsidae , related to katydids .
The Clymene dolphin ( Stenella clymene ) , in older texts known as the short - snouted spinner dolphin , is a dolphin endemic to the Atlantic Ocean .
Archips is a genus of tortrix moths the tribe Archipini .
Tylochromis is a genus of African fishes in the family Cichlidae .
The Taiwan salamander , Hynobius formosanus , is a species of salamander in the Hynobiidae family , endemic to Taiwan , where it occurs in the high mountains at around 2,100 m ( 6,900 ft ) .
The Hartlaub 's turaco ( Tauraco hartlaubi ) is a species of bird in the Musophagidae family .
Thermotogae is a phylum of the domain `` Bacteria '' .
Asparagoideae is a subfamily of monocot flowering plants in the family Asparagaceae , order Asparagales , according to the APG III system of 2009 .
Macromaxillocaris bahamaensis is a species of stenopodidean shrimp , the only species in the family Macromaxillocarididae .
Coreinae is a subfamily of the hemipteran insect family Coreidae .
Wikstroemia is a genus of 55 - 70 species of flowering shrubs and small trees in the mezereon family , Thymelaeaceae .
The Davao squirrel ( Sundasciurus davensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Achenoderus octomaculatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Achenoderus .
Tropiocolotes is a genus of geckos that grow to about 2 `` in length and are endemic to Northern Africa .
The Pacific horned frog ( Ceratophrys stolzmanni ) is a species of frog in the Ceratophryidae family .
Lissoceras is an involute , smooth or finely vetrolaterally ribbed , ammonite with a blunt , un - keeled venter , included in the Haploceratidae , that lived from the Lower Bajocian - Middle Oxfordian ( Middle to Upper Jurassic ) in what is now Europe , south Asia , and southern Alaska .
Gongora , abbreviated Gga in horticultural trade , is a member of the Orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) .
The Bolivian slaty antshrike ( Thamnophilus sticturus ) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae .
The Round scad , Decapterus punctatus , is a species of fish in the Carangidae .
The Rhynchonellata is a class of Lower Cambrian to Recent articulate brachiopods that combines orders from within the Rhynchonelliformea ( Articulata revised ) with well developed pedicle attachment .
Discinidae is a family in the brachiopods superfamily Discinoidea .
Tubbia , is a genus of the family Centrolophidae .
The Socotra cisticola or island cisticola ( Cisticola haesitatus ) is a species of bird in the Cisticolidae family .
Paraprobatius bucki is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Paraprobatius .
Lobocla is a genus of skippers in the family Hesperiidae subfamily Eudaminae
Folinella is a genus of minute sea snails , pyramidellid gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Pyramidellidae within the tribe Chrysallidini .
Echinocardium is a genus of sea urchins of the family Loveniidae , known as heart urchins .
Iratusaurus is an extinct genus of dissorophoidean euskelian temnospondyl within the family Dissorophidae .
The Yazoo darter ( Etheostoma raneyi ) is a species of darter endemic to north - central Mississippi in the United States , where it is found only in tributaries of the Little Tallahatchie and Yocona rivers .
Trichognathus marginipennis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Trichognathus .
Pellonulinae is a subfamily of freshwater herrings belonging to the family Clupeidae .
The Indian swiftlet , or Indian edible - nest swiftlet , ( Aerodramus unicolor ) is a small swift .
Neocogniauxia is a genus of orchids , ( family Orchidaceae ) , consisting of two species in the Greater Antilles .
Neoscortechinia is a plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1897 .
Oocorys is a genus of large , deepwater sea snails , marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cassidae , the helmet snails and bonnet snails .
The Coiban mastiff bat ( Molossus coibensis ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae .
Laelaptoseius is a monotypic genus of mites in the family Ascidae , endemic to New Zealand .
Virola is a genus of medium - sized trees native to the South American rainforest and closely related to other Myristicaceae , such as nutmeg .
Miocryptorhopalum kirkbyae is a species of beetle in the family Dermestidae , the only species in the genus Miocryptorhopalum .
The Spicipalpia are a suborder of Trichoptera , the caddisflies .
Thomas 's shrew tenrec ( Microgale thomasi ) is a species of mammal in the family Tenrecidae .
Aphatum rufulum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Aphatum .
The Mexican spider monkey ( Ateles geoffroyi vellerosus ) , is a subspecies of Geoffroy 's spider monkey , a type of New World monkey , from Mexico and Central America , native to Mexico , Guatemala , Honduras , Nicaragua and El Salvador .
Although Horsfield 's tarsier was usually placed in the genus Tarsius with all other living tarsiers , it is quite distinct from the Philippine tarsier and the various tarsiers of Sulawesi and nearby islands ; therefore , scientists have placed it in a separate genus , Cephalopachus .
Hasseltiopsis is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the willow family , Salicaceae .
Emileia is included in the family Otoitidae and superfamily Stephanocerataceae of the Ammonitina
Cottus schitsuumsh , commonly known as the Cedar sculpin , is a small , large - headed species of cottid that is found in the Coeur d'Alene and St. Joe rivers in northern Idaho , and in a stretch of the Clark Fork river in western Montana .
The Red Sea sailfin tang or Desjardin 's sailfin tang ( Zebrasoma desjardinii ) is a marine reef tang in the fish family Acanthuridae .

The Brazilian teal or Brazilian duck ( Amazonetta brasiliensis ) is the only duck in the genus Amazonetta .

Platynerita is a genus of submarine cave snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Neritiliidae .

Progonostola is a genus of moth in the family Geometridae , native to Hawaii .
Caryophylliina is a suborder of stony corals , order Scleractinia .
Callyspongia is a demosponge genus in the family Callyspongiidae .
The Andean swift ( Aeronautes andecolus ) is a species of swift in the Apodidae family .
Cochlicellidae is a family of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Helicoidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Niphargus is by far the largest genus of its family , the Niphargidae , and the largest of all freshwater amphipod genera .
Thiara is a genus of freshwater snails , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Thiaridae .
Petrobacter is a genus of gram - negative , non - spore - forming bacteria from the family of Rhodocyclaceae which belongs to the class of Betaproteobacteria .
Ectropis is a genus in the geometer moth family ( Geometridae ) .
Trisyngyne nuda was known as Nothofagus nuda prior to 2013 .
Setulipes is a genus of fungus in the Marasmiaceae family .
Polycestaxia howas is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Polycestaxia .
The Bryopsida constitute the largest class of mosses , containing 95 % of all moss species .
The Niangara free - tailed bat ( Mops niangarae ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae .
Synthetoceratini is an extinct tribe of the subfamily Synthetoceratinae within the family Protoceratidae belonging to the order Artiodactyla endemic to North America during the Miocene , living epoch 20.6 - -4.9 Ma , existing for approximately 15.7 million years .
Robbins 's yellow bat ( Scotophilus nucella ) is a species of vesper bat .
Spirostreptus is a genus of giant millipedes of the family Spirostreptidae .
The Ceylon krait or Sri Lankan krait ( Bungarus ceylonicus ) is a species of venomous elapid snake which is endemic to the island Sri Lanka , locally known as මුදු කරවලා ( mudu karawalaa ) .
Mesoniviridae is a member of the order Nidovirales , an order of + ssRNA viruses with animal hosts .
Recluzia is a genus of small to medium - sized pelagic or planktonic sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Janthinidae .
Percopsidae is a family of fish in the order Percopsiformes , with one extant genus with two species , both endemic to North America , and two known fossil genera .
Linderniaceae is a family of flowering plants in the order Lamiales , which consists of about 13 genera and 195 species from worldwide , mainly in neotropics .
Heterochordariaceae is a brown algae family in the order Ralfsiales .
The Sclater 's whistler ( Pachycephala soror ) is a species of bird in the Pachycephalidae family .
Harpactorini is a tribe of the Harpactorinae ( assassin bugs ) .
Syphonota geographica , or the geographic sea hare , is a species of sea slug or sea hare , a marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Aplysiidae , the sea hares .
Discoglypremna is a plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1911 .
Plentuisa vendia is a species of land snail in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .

Anzor Kiknadze ( Georgian : ანზორ კიკნაძე , Russian : Анзор Леванович Кикнадзе , 26 March 1934 -- 17 November 1977 ) was a Georgian judoka who won a bronze medal in the heavyweight division ( + 80 kg ) at the 1964 Summer Olympics .
George Ahlgren ( August 16 , 1928 -- December 30 , 1951 ) was an American rower who competed at the 1948 Summer Olympics .
Paweł Woźniak ( born March 5 , 1969 in Zielona Góra , Lubuskie ) is a former hurdler from Poland , who represented his native country at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona , Spain .
Tauno Ilmoniemi ( ne Granit ) ( 16 May 1893 -- 21 September 1934 ) was a Finnish gymnast and diver who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics .
Rosario Parmegiani ( born March 12 , 1937 in Naples ) is an Italian water polo player who competed in the 1960 Summer Olympics and in the 1964 Summer Olympics .
Adolf Nilsen ( March 3 , 1895 -- October 1983 ) was a Norwegian - American rower who competed in the 1920 Summer Olympics .
Ryan Bedford ( born October 20 , 1986 in Yuma , Arizona ) is an American speed skater who competed at the 2010 Winter Olympics .
On 19 November 2011 , Macedonian Radio Television invited Kaliopi to represent Macedonia in the Eurovision Song Contest 2012 in Baku , Azerbaijan .
Alain Sarteur ( born 17 June 1946 in Plailly , Oise , France ) is a French former athlete who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Tatiana Shchegoleva is a Russian basketball player who competed for the Russian National Team at the 2008 Summer Olympics , winning the bronze medal .
Brian Field ( 15 December 1934 -- 27 April 1979 ) was a solicitor 's clerk who was one of the masterminds of the Great Train Robbery .
Thomas Domian ( born 5 July 1964 ) is a retired West German competition rower who won a gold medal in the coxed eights event at the 1988 Summer Olympics .
John Henry Jonsson ( 12 May 1912 -- 9 March 2001 ) was a Swedish runner who won a bronze medal over 5000 m at the 1936 Summer Olympics .

Gebmund was a medieval Bishop of Rochester .
Claudia Bandion - Ortner ( born 30 November 1966 ) is an Austrian judge and politician , who served as the minister of justice .

Käte Strobel joined the SPD in 1925 , being part of the party 's leadership from 1958 to 1971 while from 1949 to 1972 being a member of the German Bundestag .

Raymond Couderc ( born 16 September 1946 in Bordeaux ) is a French politician , and a member of the Senate of France , representing the Department of Hérault .

William Alexander Conn ( 1814 - - January 4 , 1903 ) was an American businessman , landowner and politician , serving as a member of the California State Assembly and as a Californian State Senator .

Jean - Gilles du Coëtlosquet ( 15 September 1700 , Saint - Pol - de - Léon -- 21 March 1784 , Paris ) was a French ecclesiastic , bishop of Limoges and preceptor to the grandchildren of Louis XV .
Gerard de Namur ( died 1155 ) was a cardinal born in Namur in the modern - day Belgium .
Joseph Michael Sullivan ( March 23 , 1930 -- June 7 , 2013 ) was an American priest and later Auxiliary bishop of the Diocese of Brooklyn , New York in the Roman Catholic Church from 1980 to 2005 .
Robert Stockton Green ( March 25 , 1831 -- May 7 , 1895 ) was an American Democratic Party politician , who served as the 27th Governor of New Jersey from 1887 - -1890 .
Jean Sarazin ( also Sarrasin or Sarrazin ) , Latinized Joannes Saracenus ( 1539 - -1598 ) was an abbot of the Benedictine Abbey of St. Vaast , Arras , and the third archbishop of Cambrai .
Herman Roethel ( January 3 , 1882 -- February 17 , 1956 ) was a Wisconsin farmer from Kiel , Wisconsin , USA , who served two terms as a member of the Wisconsin State Assembly , first being elected as a Socialist , and later as a Republican .
On July 29 , 1853 , Louis de Goesbriand was appointed the first bishop of the newly erected Diocese of Burlington , Vermont , by Pope Pius IX . He received his episcopal consecration on the following October 30 from Archbishop Gaetano Bedini , with Bishops John McCloskey and Louis Amadeus Rappe serving as co - consecrators .
Cliff Rosenberger ( born April 21 , 1981 ) is a member of the Ohio House of Representatives , serving the 91st District since 2011 .
Albert Edward Matthews ( May 17 , 1873 -- December 16 , 1949 ) was the 16th Lieutenant Governor of Ontario .
Lewis T. Mittness , Jr. was a former member of the Wisconsin State Assembly .
Hudjefa I is the cartouche name and pseudonym of a king ( pharaoh ) who is said to have ruled during the Ancient Egyptian 2nd dynasty .
Geetha Gopi ( Malayalam : ഗീത ഗോപി ; born 30 May 1973 ) is an Communist Party of India politician from Thrissur and Member of the Kerala Legislative Assembly from Nattika Assembly Constituency .
The Allied Military Government of Occupied Territories ( AMGOT ) , looking for anti - fascist notables to replace fascist authorities , made Don Calogero Vizzini mayor of Villalba , as well as an Honorary Colonel of the US Army .
Blessed Carlo Liviero was an Italian Roman Catholic bishop who led the Diocese of Città di Castello .
Earl Ray Tomblin ( born March 15 , 1952 ) is an American Democratic Party politician and the 35th and current Governor of West Virginia .
Alphonse Georger ( born 25 May 1936 in Sarreguemines , Moselle ( department ) , is a French and Algerian Catholic bishop and an Emeritus Bishop of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Oran in Algeria since December 2012 .
Hamilton Richardson ( October 17 , 1820 -- ? ) was an American businessman from Janesville , Wisconsin who spent one year ( 1864 ) as a member of the Wisconsin State Assembly and six years ( 1877 - -1882 ) as a Republican member of the Wisconsin State Senate from Rock County , Wisconsin .
Jacopo Contarini ( 1194 - 1280 ) was the 47th Doge of Venice , from 6 September 1275 to his abdication on 6 March 1280 .
Silvério Paulo de Albuquerque , O.F.M. ( March 11 , 1917 -- May 28 , 2013 ) was a Brazilian bishop of the Roman Catholic Church .
Hernando de Talavera ( Talavera de la Reina , Spain , 1428 -- Granada , Spain , 14 May 1507 ) was a Spanish monk of the Order of Saint Jerome , of converso origins , who became archbishop of Granada and confessor of Queen Isabela .
Henri Namphy ( born November 2 , 1932 in Cap - Haïtien , Haiti ) was a Haitian general and political figure who served as President of Haiti 's interim ruling body , the National Council of Government , from February 7 , 1986 to February 7 , 1988 .
Saint Euthymius of Tarnovo ( also Evtimiy ; Bulgarian : Свети Евтимий Търновски , Sveti Evtimiy Tarnovski ) was Patriarch of Bulgaria between 1375 and 1393 .
Joseph B. Willigers ( October 26 , 1930 -- September 30 , 2012 ) was the Roman Catholic bishop of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Jinja in Jinja , Uganda .
Margrethe Vestager ( born 13 April 1968 at Glostrup , Zealand ) is a Danish politician , who is currently serving as the ( European Commissioner for Competition ) .
Qin Hui or Qin Kuai ( January 17 , 1090 - -November 18 , 1155 ) was a Chancellor of the Song dynasty in Chinese history .
Roberto Dipiazza ( born February 1 , 1953 in Aiello del Friuli , Province of Udine ) is an Italian entrepreneur and politician , mayor of Muggia ( in the Province of Trieste ) in 1996 - 2001 , and mayor of Trieste in 2001 - 2011 .
Jules Maaten was elected as a member of the European Parliament in the European Elections of 10 June 1999 , on the list of the Dutch Liberal Party VVD and he joined the Liberal Group in the Parliament .

Pholistoma racemosum is a species of flowering plant in the borage family which is known by the common name racemose fiesta flower .
Chiropsalmus quadrumanus , commonly known as the four - handed box jellyfish , is a species of box jellyfish in class Cubozoa .
Geopora cooperi , commonly known as the pine truffle or the fuzzy truffle , is a species of fungus in the family Pyronemataceae .
Keckiella antirrhinoides ( formerly Penstemon antirrhinoides ) is a species of flowering shrub in the plantain family known by the common names snapdragon penstemon and chaparral beardtongue .
Auerodendron pauciflorum is a rare species of flowering plant in the Rhamnaceae family .
Pseudamnicola anteisensis is a species of small brackish water snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrobiidae .
Lethrinus laticaudis , the Grass emperor , is a species of emperor native to the western Pacific Ocean where they occur on coral reefs at depths of from 5 to 35 metres ( 16 to 115 ft ) .
Phacus is a genus of unicellular protists , of the phylum Euglenozoa ( also known as Euglenophyta ) .
Isocoma acradenia is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name alkali goldenbush .
Paphiopedilum niveum is a species of orchid occurring from peninsular Thailand to peninsular Malaysia .
Polymesoda maritima , or the maritime marsh clam , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Corbiculidae .
The sand darters , family Kraemeriidae , are a small family ( about 9 species ) of Perciformes fishes native to the Indian Ocean to the central Pacific Ocean .
Baviola is a genus of jumping spiders with three described species .
Kirgizemys is an extinct genus of turtle from Early Cretaceous of China , Mongolia , Russia and Kyrgyzstan .
Philaeus chrysops is a species of jumping spider ( Salticidae ) .
Lampropeltis getula , commonly known as the eastern kingsnake , common kingsnake , or chain kingsnake ( more ) , is a harmless colubrid species endemic to the United States and Mexico .
Pinguicula primuliflora ( /ˌpɪˈŋgwɪkjələ ˌpɹɪmjʊləˈfloːɹə/ ) , commonly known as the southern butterwort or primrose butterwort , is a species of carnivorous plant belonging to the genus Pinguicula .
Hypericum olympicum ( Mount Olympus St. John 's wort ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Hypericaceae .
Mahonia cardiophylla is a shrub in the Berberidaceae described as a species in 2001 .
Cyathea hooglandii is a species of tree fern native to the Western Highlands of New Guinea , where it grows in mossy forest at an altitude of about 3000 m. The trunk of this plant is erect , up to 3 m tall and approximately 10 cm in diameter .
Canobius is an extinct genus of early ray - finned fish that lived in the Carboniferous period of Europe .
Blechnum spicant is a species of fern in the family polypodiaceae , known by the common names hard - fern or deer fern .
Turbonilla indispensabilis is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae .
Medauroidea extradentata , commonly known as the Vietnamese or Annam walking stick , is a species of the family Phasmatidae .
Excoecaria agallocha , a mangrove species , belongs to the genus Excoecaria of the family Euphorbiaceae .
Leptodactylus wagneri ( common name : Wagner 's white - lipped frog ) is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family .
Ornithocephalus falcatus is a species of orchid found from the Guianas , Venezuela , Ecuador , and Peru .
Cimoliornis is a pterosaur genus containing the single species Cimoliornis diomedeus .
Lythrurus roseipinnis , the cherryfin shiner , is a species of fish native to Mississippi , Alabama , and Louisiana in the southeastern United States .
Thylacodes squamigerus , common name the scaled wormsnail , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Vermetidae , the worm snails .
Conus nimbosus , common name the stormy cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Hemidactylus reticulatus , commonly known as the Reticulated Leaf - toed Gecko , is a species of terrestrial , nocturnal , insectivorous gecko found in rocky areas of South India .
Aristolochia tomentosa is a species of flowering plant in the Aristolochiaceae family .
Paracroton zeylanicus is a species of flowering plant in the family Euphorbiaceae that is endemic to south - western parts of Sri Lanka .
Rubus paludivagusis a rare North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Megacephala ion is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Sumlin in 1997 .
Agrianthus is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae described as a genus in 1836 .
Aromobates , sometimes known as the skunk frogs , is a genus of frogs from the Andes of Venezuela and Colombia .
Haliotis brazieri , common name Brazier 's ear shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Ribes watsonianum is a North American species of currant known by the common names spring gooseberry and wild gooseberry .
Cophoscincopus ( common name : keeled water skinks ) is a genus of skinks endemic to West Africa .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Laricina mollis .
Chilonopsis blofeldi was a species of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Subulinidae .
Vesperus sanzi is a species of beetle in the Vesperidae family that can be found in Portugal and western Spain .
Dendropsophus columbianus ( common name : Boettger 's Colombian treefrog ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Lyncina sulcidentata , common name the Square Toothed Cowry or Groove Toothed Cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Longitarsus alfierii is a species of beetle in the Galerucinae subfamily that can be found in such European countries as Bulgaria , Greece , Republic of Macedonia , Spain , Ukraine , Yugoslavia , and on Crete .
Dryinus grimaldii is an extinct species of wasp in the dryinid genus Dryinus .
Thelephora is a genus of fungi in the family Thelephoraceae .
Engina tuberculosa is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Lepidothamnus intermedius ( Yellow Silver Pine ) is a species of conifer in the Podocarpaceae family .
Weberocereus is genus of cacti .
Sauropelta ( /ˌsɔːroʊˈpɛltə/ SAWR - o - PEL - tə ; meaning ' lizard shield ' ) is a genus of nodosaurid dinosaur that existed in the Early Cretaceous Period of North America .
Baccharoides is a genus of Asian and African plants in the evil tribe within the sunflower family .
Multiclavula vernalis is a species of clavarioid fungus in the family Clavulinaceae .
Crepis pannonica ( pasture hawksbeard ) is a European species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Crataegus pruinosa is a species of hawthorn known by the common name frosted hawthorn .
Japalura is a genus of lizards in the family Agamidae .
Salix eriocarpa is a species of willow native to wet lowlands of Japan .
Phoebe chekiangensis is a species of tree up to 20 metres ( 66 ft ) in the Lauraceae family .
Cerithidea valida is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Potamididae .
Stephanostegia is a genus of plant in family Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1888 .
Boleophthalmus dussumieri is a species of mudskipper native to the Indian Ocean where it can be found on mudflats in fresh , brackish and marine waters of Iraq , Pakistan and India as well as probably in Bangladesh .
The Bengal mongoose ( Herpestes javanicus palustris ) is a subspecies of the small Asian mongoose .
Lobophyllia corymbosa , the lobed cactus coral or brain root coral , is a species of large polyp stony coral in the family Lobophylliidae .
Myosotis nemorosa ( syn . Myosotis strigulosa ) is a plant species of the genus Myosotis .
Gongora aceras is a species of orchid found in Colombia and western Ecuador .

Saulea is a genus of freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Ampullariidae , the apple snails .

Elaphoglossum pattersoniae is a very rare species of fern that grows in Peru .
Millettia leucantha or sathon is a species of plant in the Fabaceae family .
Haliotis ovina , common name the sheep 's ear abalone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Synechocystis is a genus of unicellular , freshwater cyanobacteria primarily represented by the strain Synechocystis sp . PCC6803 .
Lilium fargesii is a Chinese species of plants in the lily family native to Hubei , Shaanxi , Sichuan and Yunnan provinces of China .

Odonteleotris is a small genus of sleeper gobies native to tropical marine waters of the western Pacific Ocean and fresh and brackish waters of southern Asia .
Thalotia conica , common name the conical top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .

Rhadinosticta banksi is an Australian species of damselfly in the family Isostictidae , commonly known as the northern wiretail .
Dialommus fuscus , the Galápagos four - eyed blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny endemic to the coasts of the Galapagos Islands .
Aloe aldabrensis ( previously Lomatophyllum aldabrensis ) is a species of Aloe endemic to the islands of Aldabra in the Indian Ocean , where it can still be found in coastal scrub on limestone - based soil .
Macropomoides is an extinct genus of lobe - finned fish which lived during the Cretaceous period .
The Datiscaceae are a family of Dicotyledonous plants , containing two species of the genus Datisca .
Orestias parinacotensis is a species of fish in the Cyprinodontidae family .
Nodularia is a genus of filamentous nitrogen - fixing cyanobacteria , or blue - green algae .
Lophozozymus pulchellus is a species of crab in the family Xanthidae .
As of August 2013 the World Checklist of Selected Plant Families recognises the single species Schizozygia coffaeoides .
Enhydrocyon basilatus is an extinct species of bone crushing hesperocyonid dog that lived during the Late Oligocene to Miocene living from 24.8 - -20.6 Ma and existed for approximately 4.2 million years .
Some experts divide Agrocybe pediades into several species , mainly by habitat and microscopic features , such as spore size .
Clinids are blennioids ; perciform marine fish of the family Clinidae .
The Austin blind salamander ( Eurycea waterlooensis ) is an endangered species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae , endemic to Barton Springs in Austin , Texas , United States .
Dendrobium taurinum , the Bull Orchid , is a species of flowering plant in the Orchidaceae family .
The genus contains the single species Gigantiops destructor , which is also the sole member of the tribe Gigantiopini .

Xenochrophis is a genus of colubrid snakes endemic to Asia .

Melica bocquetii , is a species of grass in the Poaceae family endemic to the Subbaetic System of southern Spain .

Chiloglanis kazumbei is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Tanzania , where it occurs in the lower Malagarasi River and the Luiche River .

Chrosiothes is a spider genus that occurs almost exclusively in the New World from the USA to Brazil , with one species found in China , Korea and Japan , and two species endemic to Taiwan .

Ribes glandulosum , the skunk currant , is a North American species of flowering plant in the currant family .

Paranarsia joannisiella is a species of moth in the family Gelechiidae .
Eugenia abbreviata is a species of plant in the Myrtaceae family .
Mitromorpha is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Mitromorphidae , in the superfamily Conoidea the cone snails and their allies .
Styloleptoides inflaticollis is a species of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae , and the only species in the genus Styloleptoides .
Electroatopos castaneus is an extinct species of ant - like stone beetle , described in 2010 , and the only species in the genus Electroatopos .
Rhyothemis variegata , known as the common picture wing or variegated flutterer , is a species of dragonfly of the family Libellulidae , found in South Asia .
Opsimus quadrilineatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Opsimus .
Allococalodes cornutus is a jumping spider species in the genus Allococalodes endemic to New Guinea .
The mud elimia , scientific name Pleurocera alabamensis , is a species of freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an gastropod mollusk in the family Pleuroceridae .
Inocybe godeyi is a species of Inocybaceae fungus found in Europe .
Lyrocladius is a genus of chironomid midges that belongs to the subfamily Orthocladiinae and is composed of a single species , Lyrocladius radulatus Mendes et Andersen ( 2008 ) , described from Brazil .
Mixophyes hihihorlo is a species of frog in the Myobatrachidae family .
Diandongosaurus is an extinct genus of eosauropterygian known from the lower Middle Triassic ( Anisian age ) of Yunnan Province , southwestern China .
Morelladon is an extinct genus of herbivorous styracosternan ornithopod dinosaur , that lived during the Early Cretaceous of Spain , around 130 million years ago .
Amorphoscelis siebersis is a species of praying mantis found in Borneo .
Euphorbia fendleri is a species of euphorb known by the common name Fendler 's sandmat .
Proplanicoxa is a genus of iguanodont dinosaur which existed in what is now England during the Early Cretaceous period ( late Barremian stage , around 126 mya ) .
Carex appropinquata , known as fibrous tussock - sedge , is a species of flowering plant in the family Cyperaceae , commonly known as sedges .
Serranus tigrinus is a species of fish in the family Serranidae , which includes the groupers .
Carex spissa is a species of sedge known by the common name San Diego sedge .
Rubus burnhamii , Burnham 's blackberry , is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Callochromis melanostigma is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it prefers sandy bottoms with nearby rocks .
Nothoscordum bivalve is a species of flowering plant in the Amaryllidaceae known by the common names crowpoison and false garlic .
Van Deusen 's rat ( Rattus vandeuseni ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Tabernanthe is a genus of flowering plants in the dogbane family , Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1888 .
Macrobrachium carcinus is a species of freshwater shrimp native to streams , rivers and creeks from Florida to southern Brazil .
Agave eggersiana is an endangered species of spiky plant which grows in the Virgin Islands , in dry , exposed areas .
The North American cougar ( Puma concolor couguar ) , is the cougar subspecies once commonly found in eastern North America and still prevalent in the western half of the continent .
Macroparalepis affinis is a species of fish which belongs to the Paralepididae(barracudas ) family .
Ungaliophis panamensis , or the Panamanian dwarf boa , is a species of snake in the Tropidophiidae family .
The Badlands bighorn , Ovis canadensis auduboni , also commonly known as Audubon 's bighorn sheep , is an extinct subspecies of bighorn sheep of the northern Great Plains in North America .
Eriocraniidae is a family of moths restricted to the Holarctic region , with six extant genera .
Plesiopleurodon is an extinct genus of plesiosauroid from the Late Cretaceous of North America .
Arachnocoris trinitatis is a true bug species found in Trinidad , West Indies .
Neoplecostomus microps ( LDA034 ) is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it occurs in the Paraíba do Sul River basin .
Endamoeba is a genus of amoeboids in Amoebozoa .
Cryptocentrum latifolium is a member of the Orchid family , the largest species in genus Cryptocentrum .
Amanita rubrovolvata , commonly known as the red volva Amanita , is a species of fungus in the Amanitaceae family .
Glebocarcinus is a genus of crabs formerly included in the genus Cancer , containing two species :
Calliostoma psyche , common name the psyche top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Avolatavis is an extinct genus of stem - parrot ( pan - psittaciform ) known from the early Eocene Fossil Butte Member of the Green River Formation of Wyoming , USA .
Terminalia australis Cambess is a South American species of large shrub or tree , which reaches up to 12 m in height and 40 cm in diameter .
Hescheleria is an extinct genus of thalattosaurian marine reptile from the Middle Triassic ( 247.2 to ~235 Ma ) of Monte San Giorgio in Switzerland .
The specimen was correctly identified as a different species and renamed Rhyniognatha hirsti in 1928 by entomologist Robin J. Tillyard .
Chlidanthus is a genus that consists of 10 species of tender bulbs from tropical South America , mostly natives to the Andes .
Stenamma alas is a species of ant which can be found in wet forests of Costa Rica on an elevation of 50 - -1,600 metres ( 160 - -5,250 ft ) .
Amblydoras monitor is a species of thorny catfish that occurs in the upper Amazon Basin where it can be found in the countries of Brazil , Colombia and Peru .
Asplenium daghestanicum , the Dagestanian spleenwort , is a species of spleenwort that is endemic to Dagestan in Russia .
Sulpitus lilla is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Sulpitus .
Recilia rugulans is a species of bug from Cicadellidae family that can be found in South Africa and Swaziland .
Platysomus is an extinct genus of ray - finned fish that lived in the Carboniferous and Permian periods .
Belonophago is a small genus of distichodontid freshwater fish found in Middle Africa .
Quercus tardifolia , the Chisos Mountains oak or lateleaf oak , is a rare North American species of trees in the beech family .
It contains the single species Ateucheta zatesima , which is found in Australia .
Cantharellus lateritius , commonly known as the smooth chanterelle , is a species of edible fungus in the Cantharellaceae family of mushrooms .
Ummidia aedificatoria is a trapdoor spider species found in Portugal , Spain and Morocco .
Neanura muscorum is a species of Collembola in the family Neanuridae and subfamily Neanurinae .
Callytron alleni is a species of ground beetles in the genus Callytron .
Conus kerstitchi , common name Kerstitch 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
