Naucleeae is a tribe of flowering plants in the Rubiaceae family and contains about 183 species in 24 genera .
Lycogala epidendrum , commonly known as wolf 's milk , groening 's slime is a cosmopolitan species of plasmodial slime mould which is often mistaken for a fungus .
Favonigobius lateralis is a species of goby native to coastal waters of eastern Australia , Tasmania and New Zealand where it can be found in marine and brackish waters of sandy estuaries .
Paxistima is a small genus of shrubs in the bittersweet family containing two North American species .
Arborophilinae is a bird subfamily containing the jungle- and wood partridges .
Alosa saposchnikowii , or the saposhnikovi shad , is a species of fish in the clupeid genus Alosa .
Acalypha eremorum is a species of shrubs of the plant family Euphorbiaceae , endemic to Queensland , Australia .
Osmoderma eremita , the hermit beetle or Russian leather beetle , is a species of European beetle in the Scarabaeidae family .
Cacozelia elegans is a snout moth species in the genus Cacozelia .
Notostira erratica is a species of bugs from a Miridae family , subfamily Mirinae that can be found everywhere in Europe except for Azores , Benelux , Faroe Islands , Madeira , Malta , and African and Asia ones such as Canary Islands and Cyprus .
Aricoris is a genus in the butterfly family Riodinidae present in the Neotropical ecozone .
Ambastaia nigrolineata is a vulnerable species of loach found in the Mekong basin in southeast Asia .
Notophycis is a genus of morid cods .
†Oleacina guadeloupensis was a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Oleacinidae .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Xylogone sphaerospora .
The Chlopsidae , or false morays , are a family of eels found in coral reefs worldwide .
Lepilaena is a genus of aquatic and marine flowering plant comprising 6 or more species endemic to coastal and brackish or akaline inland waters of temperate Australia , Tasmania , and New Zealand .
Zulmasuchus ( meaning `` Zulma Gasparini 's crocodile '' ) is an extinct genus of sebecid sebecosuchian mesoeucrocodylian .
Miopetaurista is an extinct genus of flying squirrel closely related to flying squirrels of today .
Catfish ( or catfishes ; order Siluriformes ) are a diverse group of ray - finned fish .
Rhynchobatus is a group of rays commonly known as wedgefishes , and the sole genus in the family Rhynchobatidae .
Agra katewinsletae is a species of carabid beetle named after English actress and singer Kate Winslet .
Ambesa walsinghami is a species of snout moth in the genus Ambesa .
Parapsallus vitellinus is a species of plant bug belonging to the family Miridae , subfamily Phylinae , that can be found everywhere in Europe except for Albania , Andorra , Greece , Lithuania , Norway , all states of former Yugoslavia , and various European and African islands .
Penicillium sumatrense is a species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from the rhizosphere of the plant Lumnitzera racemosa .
Geophorus agglutinans is a species of tropical land snail with an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Helicinidae .
Mayaca is a genus of flowering plants , often placed in its own family , the Mayacaceae .
Bakevelliidae is an extinct family of prehistoric bivalves that lived from the Late Mississippian until the Middle Eocene .
Betta albimarginata is a species of gourami endemic to the island of Borneo , where it is only found in the Indonesian province of Kalimantan Timur .
Eupeodes corollae is a very common European species of hoverfly .
The Hemigalinae are a subfamily of the viverrids denominated and first described by John Edward Gray in 1864 .
Lentinellus montanus is a species of agaric fungus in the family Auriscalpiaceae .
Kairuku is an extinct genus of penguin .
Tapinoma karavaievi is a species of ant in the genus Tapinoma .
The family Strashilidae is an extinct group of Jurassic flies from Siberia and China .
Trichostema parishii is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name Parish 's bluecurls .
Ananteris sabineae is a species of scorpion .
Serapias neglecta , the scarce tongue - orchid , is a species of orchid endemic to southern Europe .
Ceratitis rosa , the Natal fruit fly or Natal fly , a species from the family Tephritidae of the order Diptera , is a fruit fly .
Pachnoda impressa , the Green and Yellow Fruit Chafer , is a species of beetles belonging to the Scarabaeidae family and subfamily of the Cetoniinae .
Cardiocorax is an extinct genus of elasmosaurid known from the Late Cretaceous ( early Maastrichtian stage ) Mocuio Formation of Namibe Province , southern Angola .
Parinoberyx horridus is a species of marine slimehead only known from the Western Pacific and the Coral Sea at depths around 300 m ( 980 ft ) .
The Dicranolasmatidae are a family of harvestmen with about 20 described species in a single genus .
Eleutherodactylus parapelates is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to the Massif de la Hotte , southwestern Haiti .
Chusquea elegans is a bamboo species in the genus Chusquea .
Leiokarinosuchus ( meaning `` smooth - headed crocodile '' ) is an extinct genus of neosuchian mesoeucrocodylian from the Early Cretaceous Wealden Group of southern England .
Stephanomeria is a genus of North American plants also known as wirelettuce , belonging to the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
Suillus placidus , is a species of fungus in the genus Suillus .
The parrot subfamily Psittaculinae consists of three tribes , the Polytelini with three genera , the Psittaculini or Asian psittacines , and the pygmy parrots of the Micropsittini tribe .
Elsinoë pyri is a species of fungus in the family Elsinoaceae .
Neolamprologus pulcher is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it prefers locations with plenty of sedimentation .
Ectopsocidae is a family of Psocoptera ( book lice or bark lice ) belonging to the suborder Psocomorpha .
Flabellina verrucosa , is a species of sea slug , an aeolid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Flabellinidae .
Calliostoma euglyptum , common name the sculptured top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Flourensia polyclada is a tarwort species that was first described by American botanist Sidney Fay Blake .
Stefania goini ( Vegas Falls treefrog ; Spanish : rana stefania del Duida ) is a species of frog in the family Hemiphractidae .
Deinanthe is a genus consisting of a few species of rare herbaceous - habit rhizomatous plants found in the mountain woodlands of East Asia , ranging from China to Japan .
Scutiger sikimmensis is a species of toad found in northern India , Nepal , and Tibet .
Paracyclotosaurus ( Near Wheeled Lizard ) is an extinct genus of temnospondyl amphibian , which would have appeared similar to today 's salamander -- but much larger , at up to 2.3 metres ( 7.5 ft ) long .
Miltonia russelliana , the Russell 's Miltonia , is a species of orchid occurring in southeastern and southern Brazil .
Gymnoscyphus ascitus is a species of clingfish found off of St. Vincent , Lesser Antilles , at depths of from 231 to 258 metres ( 758 to 846 ft ) .
Carpocoris mediterraneus , the Red shield bug , is a species of shield bug in the Pentatomidae family .
Cetopsidium minutum is a species of whale catfish found in Brazil , French Guiana , Guyana , Suriname and Venezuela where it occurs in the coastal rivers north of the Amazon to the Orinoco River .
Amanita volvata , also known as Volvate Amanita is a white coloured species of fungi from Amanitaceae family that can be found in southeastern United States .
Hieracium amplexicaule ( also called sticky hawkweed ) is a species of plant from Asteraceae family .
Methanoplanus endosymbiosus is a species of archaeon , an endosymbiont of the marine sapropelic ciliate Metopus contortus .
Ivanantonia is the only genus in the extinct rodent family Ivanantoniidae and is represented by a single species , Ivanantonia efremovi , from the early Eocene of Mongolia .
Grevillea hookeriana ( Red toothbrushes or Hooker 's grevillea ) is a shrub species in the family Proteaceae .
Rhombodera valida is a species of praying mantis found in Asia and nearby islands .
Spathiurus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the Campanian .
Metzgeriales is an order of liverworts .
Betadevario ramachandrani is a species of cyprinid fish that is found only in the upper Sita River , India drainage in Karnataka , India .
† Bembexia is a genus of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks .
Eobaatar is a genus of extinct mammal from the Lower Cretaceous of Mongolia and Spain .
Rabidosa punctulata , the dotted wolf spider , is a species of spider in the family Rabidosa .
Elymus lanceolatus is a species of grass known by the common names thickspike wheatgrass and streamside wheatgrass .
Ozyptila flava is a crab spider species found in Spain .
Basilichthys is a genus of Neotropical silversides native to freshwater habitats in Chile and Peru .
Conus venulatus , common name the Cape Verde cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Arginae is a subfamily of sawflies .
The Manning River snapping turtle ( Flaviemys purvisi ) is a species of turtle in the Chelidae family .
Cypriola acanthocinoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cypriola .
Ochrosia is a flowering plant genus of flowering plants , first described as a genus in 1789 .
Brachyplatys punctipes is a species of shield bugs belonging to the family Plataspidae found in China .
Skirroceras macrum is a Stephanoceratacean ( ammonite ) species belonging to the family Stephanoceratidae .
Cistus creticus ( Pink Rock - Rose , Hoary Rock - Rose ) is a species of shrubby plant in the family Cistaceae .
Centaurea calcitrapa is a species of flowering plant known by several common names , including red star - thistle and purple starthistle .
Scyllarus is a genus of slipper lobsters from the Atlantic Ocean , including the Mediterranean and Caribbean .
The gray cat snake ( Boiga siamensis ) , also known as eyed cat snake or Siamese cat snake is a species of catsnake found in northeastern India , Bangladesh , Myanmar , Cambodia , Thailand , Malaysia , and Vietnam .
Pavoraja mosaica ( common name : mosaic skate ) is a species of fish in the Rajidae family .
Orthotylus salsolae is a species of bug from the Miridae family that can be found in France , Spain , and the island of Sicily .
Eucephalus ledophyllus is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Cascade aster .
Laevisuchus ( /ˌlɛvɨˈsjuːkəs/ LEE - və - SEW - kəs , `` light crocodile '' ) is a genus of abelisauroid theropod dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous .
Nama depressum , commonly known as depressed fiddleleaf , is a species of flowering plant in the borage family .
Poecilotheria miranda , also known as the Bengal ornamental is a species of tarantula .
Kappaphycus alvarezii ( syn . K. cottonii ; Eucheuma cottonii ) is a species of red algae .
Doswellia is an extinct genus of archosauriform from the Late Triassic of North America .
The species was named to honor Asa Gray , an eminent American botanist of the mid-19th century who discovered Lilium grayi in 1840 in the Appalachian mountains on Roan Mountain .
Eupterotidae is a family of insects in the Lepidoptera order with more than 300 described species .
Skrjabinema ovis is a nematode species of the genus Skrjabinema within the Oxyuridae family .
Tonna berthae is a species of large sea snail or tun snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Tonnidae , the tun shells .
Barosaurus is monospecific , containing only the type species , B. lentus , while at least three species belong to the genus Diplodocus .
Mirapinna esau , the Hairyfish , is a species of flabby whalefish only known from the Atlantic Ocean from near the Azores .
Aemula is an extinct genus of brachiopods that lived during the Cretaceous period .
Dipturus is a large genus of skates native to the Pacific , Atlantic and Indian oceans .
Satanoperca is a small genus of cichlids from South America , where they are known from the Orinoco , Essequibo , Nickerie , Amazon , Paraná and Paraguay river basins .
Banksia ser . Prostratae is a taxonomic series in the genus Banksia .
Liolaemus is a genus of iguanian lizards , containing many species , all of which are endemic to South America .
Sphagnum girgensohnii , the Girgensohn 's bogmoss , Girgensohn 's sphagnum or common green peat moss , is a species of peat moss with a Holarctic and Indo - Malesian distribution .
Adansonia za , common name baobab , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Adansonia belonging to the Bombacaceae family .
Drosera purpurascens is a compact tuberous perennial species in the genus Drosera that is endemic to south - west Western Australia .
Conus rufimaculosus , common name the red - stained cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Stagmomantis floridensis , common name larger Florida mantis , is a species of praying mantis in genus Stagmomantis .
Schilderia achatidea , common name Agate Cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Amphiscirpus is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the sedge family containing the single species Amphiscirpus nevadensis , which is known by the common name Nevada bulrush .
Rhododendron simiarum also known as the South China Rhododendron , is one of the many species of the genus Rhododendron , which mainly grows in Southern China .
Bomarea longipes is a species of plant in the Alstroemeriaceae family .
Pseudophilautus femoralis ( commonly known as the round - snout pygmy frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Nylanderia taylori is a species of Formicinae ant found in Bangladesh , India and Sri Lanka .
Allium chinense ( commonly known as , variously Chinese onion , Chinese scallion , Japanese scallion , Kiangsi scallion , and Oriental onion ) is an edible species of onion , native to China and cultivated in many other countries .
Apocoptoma chabrillaci is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Apocoptoma .
Sibianor aurocinctus is a species of jumping spider that can be found in England ( where it was recently discovered in Hertfordshire on 29 July 2012 ) , and Palearctic .
Argylia radiata is a species of perennial plant in the Bignoniaceae family .
Obelus despreauxii is a European species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae .
Donacia dentata is a species of leaf beetles of the subfamily Donaciinae .
Juncus textilis is a species of rush known by the common name basket rush .
Arta epicoenalis is a species of snout moth in the genus Arta .
The Akun eagle - owl ( Bubo leucostictus ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae , the true owls .
Oberea bisbipunctata is a species of flat - faced longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Oberea , discovered by Pic in 1916 .
Eucryphia wilkiei is a species of rainforest shrubs growing naturally only ( endemic ) in restricted areas of cloud forests on mountain tops in the Wet Tropics region of north eastern Queensland , Australia .
Callionymus octostigmatus is a species of dragonet native to the central western Pacific Ocean where it occurs at depths of from 49 to 148 metres ( 161 to 486 ft ) .
Erophylla is a genus of bat in the family Phyllostomidae .
Leucothoe davisiae is a species of flowering plant in the heath family known by the common name Sierra laurel .
Hyalodiscus is an extant genus of diatom known also from the fossil record .
Endennasaurus is an extinct genus of thalattosaurian from the Upper Triassic of Italy .
The Ischnocera is a large suborder of lice mostly parasitic on birds but including a large family ( the Trichodectidae ) parasitic on mammals .
Spartocytisus supranubius ( supra = above ; nubius = the cloud ) is a white - flowered species of broom endemic to the Canary Islands and known there by the common name Retama del Teide .
Croton nepetifolius ( Croton nepetaefolius ) is an aromatic species of flowering plant in the spurge family , Euphorbiaceae , that is native to northeastern Brazil .
Oenothera harringtonii is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common names Arkansas Valley evening primrose and Colorado Springs evening primrose .
Only one species is currently recognized , Welfia regia .
Telonema is a genus of single - celled organisms .
Pseudischnolea kaszabi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudischnolea .
Cyathea andersonii is a species of tree fern native to India , Bhutan and southern China , where it grows in moist valleys and montane forest at an altitude of 300 - 1200 m. The trunk is erect and 6 - 10 m tall .
Balduina angustifolia ( coastal plain honeycombhead ) is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Conus dalli , common name Dall 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
The Sand Mountain blue species , E. pallescens , has been officially classified as being vulnerable , while the subspecies p. arenamontana has been labeled as critically imperiled , at great risk of extinction .
Quebradnotia is a genus of moths of the family Tortricidae .
Distichophytum is a genus of extinct vascular plants of the Late Silurian ( Ludfordian ) to Early Devonian ( Emsian ) , around 426 to 393 million years ago .
Allium schoenoprasoides is an Asian species of wild onion native to Xinjiang , Kazakhstan , Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan .
Ledra aurita is a species of bugs from Cicadellidae family .
Porcellio montanus is a species of woodlouse in the genus Porcellio belonging to the family Porcellionidae that can be found in Czech Republic , France , Italy and Switzerland .
Hemizonia clementina , known by the common name Island Tarweed , is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family , endemic to the Channel Islands of California .
Aizoanthemum is a small genus of plant in the family Aizoaceae , native to Namibia and Angola .
Galium divaricatum is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family known by the common name Lamarck 's bedstraw .
Lycaste lasioglossa is a species of terrestrial orchid native to Mexico , Honduras , Guatemala and El Salvador .
Ernstichthys intonsus is a species of banjo catfish that is endemic to Ecuador where it is found in the Napo River basin .
Ptychosperma nicolai is a species of palm in the Arecaceae family , endemic to New Guinea .
Chamberlineptus morechalensis , the sole species of the genus Chamberlineptus is a spirostreptid millipede from Venezuela .
Rhododendron spiciferum ( 碎米花 ) is a rhododendron species native to western Guizhou and Yunnan , China , where it grows at altitudes of 800 - -1900 meters .
Platinx is an extinct genus of prehistoric ray - finned fish .
Heterophallus is a genus of poeciliids native to Mexico .
Caribemys is an extinct genus of turtle which existed in the Jurassic period .
Acentronichthys leptos is the only species of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) in the genus Acentronichthys of the family Heptapteridae .
Mayariochloa is a genus of Cuban plants in the grass family .
Chiasmocleis quilombola is a species of frog native to Brazil , found between the Doce River and the Mucuri River .
Neocherentes dilloniorum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Neocherentes .
Stoebe is a genus of African plants in the pussy's - toes tribe within the daisy family .
Gephyrocharax is a genus of characins found in South America and Panama , with 13 currently recognized species :
The Bonelli 's eagle is found in hilly or mountainous habitats , with rocky walls or crags and open to wooded land , in arid to semi - moist climate , from sea level to 1500 m. Recent DNA research resulted in this species being moved to the genus Aquila from Hieraaetus .
Parhedyle cryptophthalma is a species of sea slug , an acochlidian , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusk in the family Microhedylidae .
Kalmia cuneata is a species of flowering plant in the heath family known by the common name whitewicky , sometimes spelled white - wicky or white wicky .
Otukaia rossica , common name the Russian margarite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
The fern genus Leptopteris is a small group of plants found growing in the Pacific Islands , New Guinea and Australia .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Garethjonesia lacunosispora .
Emblemaria australis is a species of chaenopsid blenny known from around Brazil , in the southwestern Atlantic ocean .
Neope armandii is a species of satyrine butterfly found in Asia .
Leonotis leonurus , also known as lion 's tail and wild dagga , is a plant species in the Lamiaceae ( mint ) family .
Lytta magister ( also known as the desert blister beetle or master blister beetle ) is a species of blister beetle found in southwestern North America .
Bythinella carinulata is a species of very small freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Amnicolidae .
Prosphyracephala is a genus of flies in the family Diopsidae .
Pinus pringlei , commonly known as Pringle 's pine , is a species of conifer in the Pinaceae family .
Pimelodus joannis is a species of catfish in the family Pimelodidae ( the long - whiskered catfishes ) endemic to Brazil , where it occurs in the Tocantins river basin .
Limacoidea is a taxonomic superfamily of medium - sized to large , air - breathing land slugs and snails .
Limax cinereoniger is a large species of air - breathing land slug in the terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk family Limacidae , the keelback slugs .
Handkea is a genus of puffball mushrooms in the family Agaricaceae .
Castilleja mendocinensis is a species of Indian paintbrush known by the common name Mendocino Coast Indian paintbrush .
Partula labrusca , was a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the Partulidae family .
Farlowella platorynchus is a species of armored catfish that occurs in the Amazon basin of Brazil and Peru .
Jinshaia sinensis is a species of loach endemic to the Yangtze and the Jinsha Jiang drainages of China .
Phyzelaphryne miriamae ( common name : Miriam 's frog ) is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family , in the monotypic genus Phyzelaphryne .
Uroteuthis bartschi , also known as Bartsch 's squid , is a species of squid growing to a known mantle length of 20 cm . It is the type species of the genus Uroteuthis .
Panonychus ulmi , the European red mite , is a species of mite which is a major agricultural pest of fruit trees .
Nemipterus furcosus , the Fork - tailed threadfin bream , also known as Rosy threadfin bream , is a species of threadfin bream native to Indian oceanic seas around Maledives , Sri Lanka , Andaman islands , and Pacific oceanic seas around Indonesia , and Australia .
Teramulus is a genus of fresh and brackish water silversides endemic to Madagascar .
Hitchcockella baronii is a species of bamboo , the only known species of the genus Hitchcockella .
Euphorbia damarana also known as Damara milk - bush and locally as melkbos is a species of flowering plant native to Namibia .
Hydatina zonata , common name the zoned paper bubble , is a species of sea snail or bubble snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Aplustridae .
Chrysogaster cemiteriorum is a European species of hoverfly which can be found feeding on umbelliferous flowers in for example damp meadows .
Prunus ceylanica is a species of plant in the family Rosaceae family .
Regina grahamii , commonly known as Graham 's crayfish snake , is a species of nonvenomous colubrid snake , which is endemic to North America .
Tibouchina urvilleana is a species of flowering plant in the family Melastomataceae , native to Brazil .
Emerita analoga , the Pacific sand crab or Pacific mole crab , is a species of small , sand - burrowing decapod crustacean found living in the sand along the temperate western coasts of America .
Plataspidae ( emended by some later authors as `` Plataspididae '' , in violation of ICZN Code Article 29.5 ) are a family of shield bugs native to the Old World .
Arctostylopida is an extinct order of placental mammals from the Late Palaeocene of Eastern Asia and North America .
Haplochromis vittatus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Kivu in East Africa .
Dactyloscopus is a genus of sand stargazers native to the coasts of the Americas .
Holcobius frater is a species of beetles in the genus Holcobius of the family Anobiidae .
Homalozoa is an extinct subphylum of Paleozoic Era echinoderms , prehistoric marine invertebrates .
Paraclione is a genus of `` sea angels '' , small floating sea slugs , pelagic marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks .
Hylyphantes is a genus of linyphiid spiders .
Macrotermes bellicosus is a species of Macrotermes .
Oligoryzomys andinus , also known as the Andean colilargo or Andean pygmy rice rat , is a species of rodent in genus Oligoryzomys of family Cricetidae .
Miyamayomena is a genus of East Asian flowering plants in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Monarda clinopodioides , common name basil beebalm , is a plant species native to Kansas , Oklahoma , Louisiana and Texas .
Chometokadmon is an extinct genus of anguimorph lizard from the Early Cretaceous of Italy .
Dasumia chyzeri is a spider species from Eastern Europe .
Sundevall 's jird , Meriones crassus , is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Pinus heldreichii ( synonym P. leucodermis ; family Pinaceae ) , or Bosnian pine , is a species of pine native to mountainous areas of the Balkans and southern Italy .
Metalasia is a genus of African flowering plants in the pussy's - toes tribe within the sunflower family .
The Polytelini tribe belongs to the parrot family Psittaculidae and consists of three genera .
Tulbaghia violacea , also known as society garlic or pink agapanthus , is a species of flowering plant in the onion family Alliaceae , indigenous to southern Africa ( KwaZulu - Natal and Cape Province ) , and reportedly naturalized in Tanzania and Mexico .
The prairie earless lizard or eastern earless lizard ( Holbrookia maculata perspicua ) is a subspecies of the lesser earless lizard , ( Holbrookia maculata ) .
Diuca is a small genus of Andean seed - eating tanagers .
Paenibacillus dendritiformis is a species of pattern - forming bacteria , first discovered in the early 90 's by Ben - Jacob 's group .
Mimobatocera laterifusca is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimobatocera .
Thricolema is a genus of leaf beetles of the subfamily Synetinae .
Mastigoteuthis is a genus of whip - lash squid containing approximately three species .
Helmetia is an extinct genus of arthropod from the Cambrian .
It contains the single species Apocrisias thaumasta , which is found in southern Arizona .
Choeromorpha vivesi is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family , that can be found in Asia in countries such as Indonesia .
Vitreorana is a genus of glass frogs that are native to South America , from the Atlantic Forest of Brazil and Argentina to Amazonia of Colombia and Ecuador and to the Venezuelan Coastal Range and the Guianas .
Sitona lepidus or clover root weevil is a species of weevil found in Europe .
Bankivia fasciata , common name the banded kelp shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Oxyeleotris is a genus of sleeper gobies mostly restricted to Australia and New Guinea , though some ( O. marmorata , O. siamensis , O. urophthalmoides and O. urophthalmus ) are found in Southeast Asia .
Limosella is a genus of flowering plants known as mudworts .
Vertigo modesta , common name the cross vertigo , is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Vertiginidae , the whorl snails .
Hardwickia is a monotypic genus of flowering plant in the subfamily Caesalpinioideae of the legumes .
Musa fitzalanii is a species of wild banana ( genus Musa ) , which was native to north - east Queensland , Australia , but is now believed to be extinct .
Procerithiidae is a taxonomic family of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Sorbeoconcha .
Teratosaurus is a genus of rauisuchians known from the Triassic Stubensandstein ( Löwenstein Formation - Norian stage ) of Germany .
The São Tomé collared fruit bat ( Myonycteris brachycephala ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .
Styan 's grasshopper warbler ( Locustella pleskei ) , also known as Pleske 's grasshopper warbler , is a species of Old World warbler in the Locustellidae family .
Pseudotribos ( `` false chewing '' ) is an extinct genus of mammal that lived in China during the Middle Jurassic some 165 million years ago , more closely related to monotremes than to placental or marsupial mammals .
Amphiprion akindynos , the Barrier Reef anemonefish is a species of anemonefish that is principally found in the Great Barrier Reef of Australia , but also in nearby locations in the Western Pacific .
Pseudosphromenus is a genus of medium - small gouramies native to south and southeast Asia .
Melica longiligulata is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that is endemic to Sichuan province of China .
Alveopora verrilliana is a species of stony coral that is found in the Red Sea , the Gulf of Aden , the northern Indian Ocean , the central Indo - Pacific , Australia , Southeast Asia , Japan , the East China Sea , the oceanic west and central Pacific Ocean and the Johnston Atoll .
The Weddel 's Bulbophyllum ( Bulbophyllum weddelii ) is a species of orchid .
Gymnopholus lichenifer is a species of beetle in the weevil family , Curculionidae .
Gonatopus clavipes is a species of small wasp in the family Dryinidae .
Echinophryne is a small genus of frogfishes .
Crataegus austromontana , commonly known as the Valley Head Hawthorn , is a very rare species of hawthorn .
Gynandromyia mesnili is a species of tachinid flies in the genus Gynandromyia of the family Tachinidae .
Parrisia is an extinct genus of legless batrachosauroidid salamander from Campanian - age rocks in the Marshalltown Formation , Monmouth County , New Jersey .
Bellator militaris , the horned searobin , is a species of searobin native to the western Atlantic Ocean where it is found at depths of from 40 to 110 metres ( 130 to 360 ft ) .
Monstera adansonii , the Adanson 's monstera or five holes plant , is a species of flowering plant from Araceae family which is widespread across much of South America and Central America .
Borrelia recurrentis is a species of Borrelia , a spirochaete bacterium associated with relapsing fever .
Masdevallia floribunda is a species of orchid found from southern Mexico to Honduras .
Shelbyoceras is a genus of Cambrian monoplacophora which was one of the genera mistaken for a cephalopod , since the characteristics differentiating monoplacophora from cephalopods are few .
Bombus fernaldae , the Fernald 's cuckoo bumblebee , is a species of cuckoo bumblebee having only males and queens , but no worker bees .
Callionymus valenciennei is a species of dragonet native to the Pacific waters around Japan and the Korean Peninsula where it occurs at depths of from 20 to 50 metres ( 66 to 164 ft ) .
Nymphaea gigantea is a species of aquatic perennial herbaceous plant native to Australia and New Guinea .
Amanita nivalis , the snow ringless amanita or mountain grisette , is a species of basidomycote fungus in the genus Amanita .
Cyphocottus is a genus of deepwater sculpins endemic to Lake Baikal in Russia .
Genetic testing suggests that Paxillus involutus may be a species complex rather than a single species .
Callionymus ogilbyi is a species of dragonet endemic to the Pacific waters off of New South Wales , Australia .
Epipleuria is a genus in the lady beetle family ( Coccinellidae ) .
Tangvayosaurus ( meaning `` Tang Vay lizard '' ) is a genus of sauropod dinosaur from the Aptian - Albian age Lower Cretaceous Grès Supérior Formation of Savannakhet , Laos .
Gloydius tsushimaensis , or the Tsushima Island pitviper , is a species of venomous snake in the Viperidae family .
Camponotus saundersi is a species of ant found in Malaysia and Brunei , belonging to the genus of Carpenter ants .
Crasodactylus punctatus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Crasodactylus .
It was described by Richter and Richter in 1926 , and the type species is Comura cometa , originally under the genus Cryphaeus by Richter in 1909 .
Aripuana is a plant genus in the gentian family , tribe Helieae , subclade Symbolanthus .
Gogangra laevis is a species of sisorid catfish found in Bangladesh where it occurs in the Jamuna and Meghna River drainages .
Sphenodiscus is an extinct genus of acanthoceratacean ammonite .
Lonchogenys ilisha is a species of characin found in the Rio Negro in Brazil and Colombia .
Arabis kazbegi , the Kazbegian rockcress , is a species of rockcress that is endemic to Georgia , and is known from Mtiuleti , the Devdaraki glacier , Mount Sabertse and Mount Kuro .
Padogobius is a genus of gobies native to fresh waters of southern Europe .
Myennis nebulosa is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Myennis of the family Tephritidae .
Araucaria angustifolia , the Paraná pine , Brazilian pine or candelabra tree ( pinheiro - do - paraná , araucária or pinheiro brasileiro ) , is a species in the conifer genus Araucaria .
Phelsuma astriata semicarinata is a subspecies of Seychelles day gecko .
Ascaris is a genus of parasitic nematode worms known as the `` small intestinal roundworms '' , which is a type of helminth .
Neolamprologus prochilus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it is only known to occur in Zambian waters in the southern part of the lake .
Ischaemum jayachandranii is a species of perennial in the Calophyllaceae family .
Namibotites argentata is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Namibotites of the family Tephritidae .
Paleoparadoxia ( `` ancient paradox '' ) is a genus of large , herbivorous aquatic mammals that inhabited the northern Pacific coastal region during the Miocene epoch ( 20 to 10 million years ago ) .
The Flos fulgida or Shining Plushblue is a species of lycaenid or blue butterfly found in Asia , including India .
Labeobarbus progenys is a species of cyprinid fish found in the African countries of Cameroon and the Congo Republic , as well as a questionable presence in Angola .
Penstemon utahensis is a species of penstemon known by the common names Utah beardtongue and Utah penstemon .
Myoxanthus seidelii is a species of orchid endemic to Brazil ( Espírito Santo ) .
Apteromantis aptera is a species of praying mantis endemic to the Iberian Peninsula .
Brachipposideros is an extinct genus of leaf - nosed bats known from Riversleigh , north - western Queensland , Australia and the Languedoc - Roussillon Region , France .
Stictoleptura trisignata is a species of longhorn beetle in the Lepturinae subfamily .
Tapiroidea is a superfamily of perissodactyls which includes the modern tapir .
Ctenomorphodes chronus is a species of stick insect endemic to southern Australia .
Cassia brewsteri , commonly known as Brewster 's Cassia , Leichhardt Bean , Cassia pea and Bean Tree is a species of leguminous shrubs or small trees , of the plant family Fabaceae .
Abracadabrella birdsville is a species of jumping spider in the genus Abracadabrella .
Amsinckia vernicosa is a species of fiddleneck known by the common name green fiddleneck .
Lorymodes australis is a species of snout moth in the genus Lorymodes .
× Haagespostoa is a hybrid genus of cacti , a natural hybrid between Haageocereus and Espostoa .
Moolgarda seheli ( bluespot mullet ) is a member of the Mugilidae family of ray - finned fish found worldwide in coastal temperate and tropical waters , and in some species in fresh water .
Drosophila grimshawi is a species of fruit fly from Hawaii , and was one of 12 fruit fly genomes sequenced for a large comparative study .
Onthophagus vacca is a species of dung beetles in the Onthophagini tribe of the wider scarab beetle family , Scarabaeidae .
Conasprella orbignyi , common name Orbigny 's ( false ) cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Springeratus is a genus of clinids found in the southwestern Pacific and western Indian Ocean .
Sminthuridae is a family of springtails of the order Symphypleona .
Leporinus obtusidens is a South American species of headstander that inhabits the basins of the Paraná River and the Río de la Plata , the Uruguay River , and the São Francisco River ( including minor rivers and tributaries like the Bermejo , Pilcomayo , Salí , Juramento , Dulce , and Uniguay ) .
Calliostomatidae is a family of sea snails within the superfamily Trochoidea and the clade Vetigastropoda .
Barbodes is a genus of small to medium - sized cyprinid fish native to tropical Asia .
Hosta nigrescens is a species of plants that belong to the family Asparagaceae .
Gobius leucomelas is a species of goby native to the western Indian Ocean where it is only known from off of the coasts of Eritrea .
Capoeta trutta , the longspine scraper , is a species cyprinid fish from the Middle East .
Codakia costata , or the costate lucine , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Lucinidae .
Archips breviplicanus , the Asiatic leafroller , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Gonyosoma cantoris is a species of snake found in the Himalayas in India ( Sikkim , Assam ) and Nepal as well as the Khasi and Garo Hills in Myanmar .
Actinomorpha is a valcouroceratid genus , Order Oncocerida , from the Middle Ordovician of central North America ( Minnesota , Wisconsin ) , named by Rousseau Flower , 1943 .
Zanclognatha zelleralis , the dusky fan - foot , is a species of moth of the family Noctuidae .
Pherallodiscus is a genus of clingfishes native to the central eastern Pacific Ocean along the coast of Mexico .
Cicindela dorsalis ( common name eastern beach tiger beetle ) is a species of tiger beetle .
Smilax aristolochiifolia , also known as gray sarsaparilla , Mexican sarsaparilla , sarsaparilla , is a species in the genus Smilax and the family Smilacaceae , native to Mexico and Central America .
The type species , Genusaurus sisteronis , is the only named species .
Iskandaria kuschakewitschi , the Kuschakewitsch loach , is a species of stone loach found in the Central Asian nations of Uzbekistan and Afghanistan .
The splittails are a genus Pogonichthys of cyprinid fish , consisting of two species native to western North America .
Solanum verrogeneum is a species of plant in the family Solanaceae .
The Hawaiian stilt ( Himantopus mexicanus knudseni ) is an endangered Hawaiian subspecies of the black - necked stilt ( H. mexicanus ) species .
Cebrennus rechenbergi , also known as the Moroccan flic - flac spider , is a species of huntsman spider indigenous to Morocco .
Trifolium albopurpureum is a species of clover known by the common name rancheria clover .
Keraudrenia is a genus of flowering plants native to Australia , New Guinea and Madagascar .
Tandonia rustica is a species of air - breathing , keeled , land slug , a shell - less terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Milacidae .
Sceloporus occidentalis occidentalis is a subspecies of the western fence lizard .
Rubellatoma is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Mangeliidae
Acanthocobitis pavonacea also known as the Spearfin loach is a species of ray - finned fish is known from northeastern India in the Ganges and Brahmaputra basins .
Ophrys ferrum - equinum , the Horseshoe Bee - orchid , is a terrestrial species of orchid native to Albania , Greece , and Turkey , including Crete and other islands of the Aegean .
Eufriesea surinamensis belongs to the tribe of Euglossine bees and as such is a species of orchid bee .
Xenopoclinus leprosus , the Leprous platanna - klipfish , is a species of clinid found along the coast of South Africa from the Orange River to Algoa Bay .
Hyphydrus is a genus of diving beetle native to the Palearctic ( including Europe ) , the Afro - tropical region , the Near East , North Africa .
Epilobium torreyi is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common names Torrey 's willowherb and brook spike - primrose .
Hypolaena fastigiata , commonly known as tassel rope - rush , is a plant species in the family Restionaceae .
Litarachna lopezae is a species of aquatic mite in the order Trombidiformes .
Impatiens niamniamensis , common name Congo cockatoo or Parrot Impatiens , is a species of flowering plant in the family Balsaminaceae .
Synbranchiformes , often called swamp eels , is an order of ray - finned fishes that are eel - like but have spiny rays , indicating that they belong to the superorder Acanthopterygii .
Megachilinae is a subfamily of bees .
Xymmer is a genus of ant in the subfamily Amblyoponinae containing the single species Xymmer muticus .
Lordhowea is a genus of flowering plants in the groundsel tribe within the daisy family .
Nonea is a genus of the borage family Boraginaceae .
Elliptio mcmichaeli is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels This species is endemic to the United States .
Diplommatina gibboni s a species of land snails with an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Diplommatinidae .
Unio cariei was a species of medium - sized freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusc in the family Unionidae .
Ribes pallidiflorum is a species in the genus Ribes native to the far east , from northeastern China to Russia ( Amur , Khabarovsk , Primorye , Sakhalin , and in the southern part of the Kamchatka Peninsula ) .
Ulva elegans is a species of seaweed in Ulvaceae family that is endemic to Morocco .
In 2008 , a taxonomic revision of western North American populations of this species was published , formally establishing it as a distinct species , Boletus rex - veris .
Nystalus is a genus of puffbird in the Bucconidae family .
Thalassoma robertsoni is a species of wrasse only known to occur in the waters around Clipperton Island .
Neocycloceras is an extinct nautiloid genus included in the Pseudorthocerida that lived during the Late Devonian and Mississippian ( early Carboniferous ) .
Nassarius speciosus , common name the purple - lipped dogwhelk or the splendid nassa , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae , the nassa mud snails or dog whelks .
Pimenta obscura ( also called Wild Pimento ) is a species of plant in the Myrtaceae family .
Cirsium hookerianum , common name Hooker 's thistle or white thistle , is a North American species of thistle native to western Canada and the northwestern United States .
Crataegus dahurica is a species of hawthorn native to northeastern Asia .
The Cixiidae are a family of fulgoroid insects , one of many families commonly known as planthoppers , distributed worldwide and comprising more than 2,000 species from over 150 genera .
Mymarilla wollastoni is a species of fairyflies endemic to the island of Saint Helena in the southern Atlantic .
Phyllomacromia contumax , the two - banded cruiser , is a species of dragonfly in the family Corduliidae that lives in sub - Saharan Africa .
Aristida chaseae is a rare species of grass known by the common name Chase 's threeawn .
Lamprima varians is a species of beetle in the Family Lucanidae , that is found from South Australia to Western Victoria .
Macronus , the tit - babblers , are a genus of birds in the Timaliidae family .
Anisakis is a genus of parasitic nematodes , which have life cycles involving fish and marine mammals .
Peltoschema is a genus of Chrysomelidae .
Shorea laeviforia is a plant species in the genus Shorea .
Kallima paralekta , commonly known as the Indian Leafwing or the Malayan Leafwing , is a species of brush - footed butterfly of the genus Kallima .
Apistoloricaria ommation is a species of armored catfish endemic to Peru where it is found in the lower Marañon River .
Reithrodontomys is the genus of groove - toothed New World harvest mice .
Mylabris phalerata is a species of blister beetle belonging to the Meloidae family .
Luciobrama macrocephalus is a species of cyprinid fish that is found in China and Vietnam .
The Chinese pangolin is one of eight species of pangolins .
Eschscholzia lobbii is a species of poppy known by the common name frying pans .
Pyrops delessertii is a species of true bug in the family Fulgoridae , in the genus Pyrops which are sometimes called as `` lanternflies '' .
Erigeron leibergii is a rare species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Leiberg 's fleabane .
Pliciloricus enigmaticus is a marine Loriciferan species of genus Pliciloricus described by Higgins & Kristensen 1986 .
Mallosia , described by Mulsant in 1847 , is a genus of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae , tribe Saperdini .
Zelippistes benhami is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Capulidae , the cap snails .
Oreolalax xiangchengensis ( Xiangcheng lazy toad or Xiangcheng toothed toad ) is a species of amphibian in the Megophryidae family .
Austrochloritis pusilla is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in thefamily Camaenidae .
Dennstaedtia is a primarily tropical genus of ferns described as a genus in 1801 .
Bostrychia is a genus of ibises in the Threskiornithidae family .
Mitragyna tubulosa is a tree species found in Peninsular India in the Western Ghats .
It consists of only one species , Cacolyces plagifera , which is found in Brazil , Venezuela , Guyana , Surinam and French Guiana .
Scotiellopsis terrestris is an algae species in the genus Scotiellopsis .
Bromus inermis is a species of the true grass family ( Poaceae ) .
Arctostaphylos catalinae , known by the common name Santa Catalina Island manzanita , is a species of manzanita native to Southern California .
Drosera erythrorhiza , the red ink sundew , is a perennial tuberous species in the carnivorous plant genus Drosera that is endemic to Western Australia .
Luzula orestera , with the common name Sierra woodrush , is a species of flowering plant in the rush family .
Chicoreus damicornis , common name the long - horned murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Polyergus lucidus is a species of slave - making ant in the subfamily Formicinae .
Gentiana septemfida ( crested gentian or summer gentian ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Gentianaceae , native to the Caucasus and Turkey .
Amalda is a genus of medium - sized sea snails , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Olividae , the olives .
Barlow 's lark ( Calendulauda barlowi ) is a species of lark in the Alaudidae family .
Peckemys is an extinct genus of turtle which existed in the Hell Creek Formation , United States during the late Cretaceous period ( Maastrichtian age ) .
Cestrum fasciculatum is a species of flowering plant in the nightshade family known by the common names early jessamine and red cestrum .
Ukrainurus is an extinct genus of pancryptobranchan urodelan known from the Miocene of Grytsiv locality , Ukraine .
Acropora nasuta is a species of branching stony coral in the family Acroporidae .
Augochlora leptoloba is a species of sweat bee in the genus Augochlora and the extinct monotypic subgenus Electraugochlora .
Lucania goodei , the bluefin killifish , is a small species of fish in the topminnow family Fundulidae .
Azotobacter is a genus of usually motile , oval or spherical bacteria that form thick - walled cysts and may produce large quantities of capsular slime .
Lucilia thatuna belongs to the family Calliphoridae , the species most commonly referred to as the blowflies , and the genus Lucilia .
Chrysobalanus is a genus of evergreen perennial shrubs to small trees , described as a genus by Linnaeus in 1753 .
Scansoriopteryx ( `` climbing wing '' ) is a genus of avialan dinosaur .
Leratiomyces is a genus of mushroom - forming basidiomycetes first proposed three times under invalid names , and finally validated in 2008 .
Tolypelepidida is an extinct order of heterostracan vertebrates .
Agrococcus jenensis is the type species of the Agrococcus genus of bacteria .
Brassia verrucosa , also known as Warty Brassia , is a species of plant in the Orchidaceae family native to Mexico , Central America ( Costa Rica , El Salvador , Guatemala , Honduras , Nicaragua ) , Venezuela , and Brazil .
Dysdera aurgitana is a spider species found in Spain .
Aacocrinus , also known as the feather star , is a genus of extinct sea lily from the Actinocrinitidae ( or Patelliocrinidae ) family .
Leptosiphon breviculus ( syn . Linanthus breviculus ) is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name Mojave linanthus .
Helisoma anceps , common name the two - ridge rams - horn , is a species of air - breathing freshwater snail , a pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails .
Xanthomonas arboricola is a species of proteobacteria .
Tugali colvillensis is a species of small sea snail or limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .
Luina hypoleuca ( littleleaf silverback ) is a species of the genus Luina and the family Asteraceae .
Nidularium itatiaiae is a plant species in the genus Nidularium .
Dudleya ingens , commonly known as Baja liveforever , is a species of Dudleya that grows to an average height of 12 in ( 30 cm ) and a width of 12 in ( 30 cm ) .
Polyporus alveolaris , commonly known as the hexagonal - pored polypore , is a species of fungus in the genus Polyporus .
Buddleja cordobensis is a species endemic to dry hillsides in the Argentine provinces of Córdoba , San Luís , and La Rioja at altitudes of 700 - -1500 m ; it was first described and named by Grisebach in 1874 .
Acampe praemorsa is a species of monopodial orchid .
Mimoniphona fasciculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimoniphona .
Hipponix climax is a species of small limpet - like sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Hipponicidae , the hoof snails .
Delias pratti is a species of butterfly in the Pieridae family .
Allium omeiense is a plant species endemic to Sichuan , China .
The Caucasian wisent ( Bison bonasus caucasicus ) was a subspecies of wisent that inhabited the Caucasus Mountains of Eastern Europe .
Hemimastodon ( `` half mastodont '' ) is an extinct genus of proboscidea from the Late Miocene deposits of the Dera Bugti Beds in Pakistan .
Manilkara valenzuelana is a species of tree or tall shrub in the Sapodilla family .
Heterololigo is a monotypic genus of squids containing the single species Heterololigo bleekeri .
Centropyge heraldi , common ' herald 's angelfish ' is a species of Marine angelfish from the Pacific Ocean that sometimes makes its way into the aquarium trade .
Xylophanes is a genus of moths in the family Sphingidae .
Jonesiaceae is a monotypic Actinobacteria family .
Streptomyces bullii is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from the Atacama Desert in Salar de Atacama in Chile .
Minthostachys is a genus of the mint family Lamiaceae , comprising aromatic scandent shrubs .
Barbus goktschaicus ( Gokcha barbel ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Barbus .
The Calycerales is a valid botanic name for an order of flowering plants .
Arenaria livermorensis , common name Livermore sandwort , is a plant species endemic to the Davis Mountains in Jeff Davis County in western Texas .
Quercus stellata ( Post oak ) is a North American species of oak in the white oak section .
Zaglossus hacketti is an extinct species of long - beaked echidna from Western Australia that is dated to the Pleistocene .
Cleptosoma clavipes is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cleptosoma .
The Chioneinae are a subfamily of limoniid crane flies .
Quercus toumeyi ( also called Toumey oak ) is a North American a species of trees and shrubs in the beech family .
Volema paradisiaca , common name : the Pear Melongena , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Melongenidae , the crown conches and their allies .
Mesonoemacheilus menoni is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Mesonoemacheilus .
It is a rare species with a ROTAP rating of 3VC- A small saprophytic plant growing to 45 cm ( 18 in ) tall on sandy soils and heathlands , Cryptostylis hunteriana is found mostly in coastal districts , south from the Gibraltar Range National Park .
The Blastocladiaceae are a family of fungi in the division Blastocladiomycota .
Galium uliginosum or fen bedstraw is a plant species of the genus Galium .
Glycine latrobeana ( clover glycine or Australian anchor plant ) is a species of perennial herb endemic to south - eastern Australia .
Georissa elegans is a species of minute cave snails , gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrocenidae of gastropod in the Hydrocenidae family .
Hydrangea robusta is a species of Hydrangea , native to China and the Himalayas .
Rissoellidae are a family of minute sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the informal group Lower Heterobranchia .
The Anoplocephalidae are a family of tapeworms containing Bertiella species and others .
Phidippus clarus is a species of jumping spider ( family Salticidae ) found in old fields throughout eastern North America .
Cyathea alpicola is a species of tree fern native to central Sumatra , where it grows in montane rain forest at an altitude of 2000 - 2750 m. The erect trunk can reach 5 m or more in height .
Drescoma cyrdipsa is a species of snout moth in the genus Drescoma .
Eugenia koolauensis , commonly known as Koʻolau Eugenia or Nioi , is a species of flowering plant in the myrtle family , Myrtaceae .
Penicillium isariiforme is an anamorph , phototropic species of the genus of Penicillium which produce secalonic acid D and F.
Alburnoides eichwaldii , the South Caspian sprilin is a fish species in the Cyprinidae family .
Hypogeophis brevis is a species of caecilian formerly included in the genus Grandisonia and found on the islands of Mahé and Silhouette in the Seychelles .
Petrolisthes laevigatus is a species of porcelain crab found in Chile and Peru .
Lapsanastrum is a genus of flowering plants in the dandelion family , native to East Asia ( China , Korea , Japan ) .
Cystopteris fragilis is a species of fern known by the common names brittle bladder - fern and common fragile fern .
Carcinus ( Greek : Καρκίνος Karkinos ) is a genus of crabs , which includes Carcinus maenas , an important invasive species , and C. aestuarii , a species endemic to the Mediterranean Sea .
Echinothrix is a genus of sea urchins which was first described in 1853 by Wilhelm Peters , a German naturalist and explorer .
Dicrossus is a genus of small cichlid fishes .
Ipsa childreni is a species of small or medium - sized sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Hexastylis naniflora is a rare species of flowering plant in the birthwort family known by the common name dwarf - flowered heartleaf .
Ingolfiellidea is a small suborder of amphipods with only two families , Ingolfiellidae and Metaingolfiellidae .
Panicoideae is the second - largest subfamily of the grasses with over 3,500 species , mainly distributed in warm temperate and tropical regions .
Cicuta bulbifera , commonly known as the bulb - bearing water - hemlock , is a plant native to North America and one of four species in the poisonous genus Cicuta .
Eremothera boothii is a species of wildflower known as Booth 's evening primrose .
Pliosauridae is a family of plesiosaurian marine reptiles from the Earliest Jurassic to the early Late Cretaceous ( Hettangian to Turonian stages ) of Australia , Europe , North America and South America .
Dapsilanthus spathaceus is a species of flowering plant of the family Restionaceae native to Australia .
Euphyllia cristata , commonly called grape coral , is a species of hard coral in the family Euphylliidae .
Poa glauca is a species of grass known by the common names glaucous bluegrass , glaucous meadow - grass and white bluegrass .
Grisollea thomassetii is a species of plant in the Stemonuraceae family .
Austrodanthonia caespitosa , known by various common names including Common Wallaby - grass , Ringed Wallaby - grass , and White - top , is a species of grass native to southern parts of Australia .
Asclepias welshii is a rare species of milkweed known by the common name Welsh 's milkweed .
Pyrgocythara plicosa , common name the plicate mangelia , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Mangeliidae .
Nakalipithecus nakayamai is a prehistoric great ape species that lived in today 's Kenya region early in the Late Miocene , 10 million years ago ( mya ) .
Pseudotriacanthus strigilifer , the Long - spined Tripodfish , is a species of Triacanthidae native to the Indian Ocean and the central western Pacific Ocean where it is found in coastal marine waters , also entering brackish waters in estuaries , at depths of from 2 to 110 metres ( 6.6 to 360.9 ft ) .
Allamanda cathartica , commonly called golden trumpet , common trumpetvine , and yellow allamanda , is a species of flowering plant of the genus Allamanda in the family Apocynaceae .
Patagopteryx is an extinct monotypic genus of birds that lived during the Late Cretaceous , around 80 mya , in what is now the Sierra Barrosa in northwestern Patagonia , Argentina .
Nemacladus ramosissimus is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name smallflower threadplant .
Coeloteuthis is a genus of belemnite , an extinct group of cephalopods .
Parthenium integrifolium is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names wild quinine , American feverfew , and Eastern feverfew .
Tropidophora semilineata was a species of land snail with a gill and an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Pomatiidae .
The Anastasia Island beach mouse ( Peromyscus polionotus phasma ) is a subspecies of the oldfield mouse of the southeastern United States .
Trichocera annulata , commonly known as the winter gnat , is a species of winter crane fly , of the order Diptera .
Hydrophis cyanocinctus , commonly called the annulated sea snake or the blue - banded sea snake , is a species of venomous sea snake in the family Elapidae .
Phyllanthus pulcher , the tropical leaf - flower , is a species in the genus Phyllanthus .
The Gerridae are a family of insects in the order Hemiptera , commonly known as water striders , water bugs , pond skaters , water skippers , or jesus bugs .
Stephanomeria diegensis is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name San Diego wirelettuce .
Chiloglanis polypogon is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Cameroon where it occurs in the Cross River .
Three horned - scaled pitviper , Protobothrops sieversorum is a species of venomous pit viper .
The Del Norte salamander ( Plethodon elongatus ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Eria javanica is a species of orchid , which is a plant .
Although little is known about Kenyapotamus , its dental pattern bore similarities to that of the genus Xenohyus , a European tayassuid from the Early Miocene .
Lithophragma affine is a species of flowering plant in the saxifrage family known by the common name San Francisco woodland star .
Prosopis affinis is a species of flowering tree in the pea family , Fabaceae , that is native to Argentina , Brazil , Paraguay , and Uruguay .
Aphthovirus ( from the Greek aphtha- , vesicles in the mouth ) is a viral genus of the family Picornaviridae .
Striatolamia is an extinct genus of sharks belonging to the family Odontaspididae .
Weaver ants or green ants ( genus Oecophylla ) are eusocial insects of the family Formicidae ( order Hymenoptera ) .
The Chinese red pika ( Ochotona erythrotis ) is a species of mammal in the family Ochotonidae .
Columbellopsis nycteis , common name : the fenestrate dove shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Columbellidae , the dove snails .
Lilaeopsis schaffneriana is a rare species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common names Schaffner 's grasswort and cienega false rush .
Falsoprosoplus luzonicus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Falsoprosoplus .
It is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Austroomphaliaster nahuelbutensis , found in temperate South America .
Carex luzulina is a species of sedge known by the common name woodrush sedge .
Libellula angelina , als known as Bekko Tombo , is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae , native to China and Japan .
Stathmopoda aposema is a species of moth of the family Oecophoridae .
Platycichla is a small disputed genus of tropical South American thrushes .
Pogonomyrmex californicus , or California harvester ant , is a species of ant in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Strigiphilus garylarsoni is a species of chewing louse found only on owls .
Aphids , also known as plant lice and in Britain and the Commonwealth as greenflies , blackflies , or whiteflies ( not to be confused with `` jumping plant lice '' or true whiteflies ) , are small sap - sucking insects , and members of the superfamily Aphidoidea .
The genus Ramaria comprises approximately 200 species of coral fungi .
Wasps of the genus Sphex ( commonly known as digger wasps ) are cosmopolitan predators that sting and paralyze prey insects .
Allobates mandelorum ( common name : Mount Turumiquire rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
Horkelia fusca is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by several common names , including pinewoods horkelia and dusky horkelia .
Apphianus yuccae is a species of beetle in the family Dermestidae , the only species in the genus Apphianus .
Leptosiphon montanus ( syn . Linanthus montanus ) is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name mustang clover .
Alopecosa kovblyuki is a wolf spider species found in Russia and Ukraine .
Borneodessus zetteli is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Borneodessus .
Discoplax is a genus of terrestrial crabs .
Astroloma foliosum , commonly known as candle cranberry , is a small shrub species in the family Ericaceae .
Micronema is a genus of sheatfishes native to the Southeast Asian region .
Gregoria fenestrata is the only member species of sea anemones in the genus Gregoria .
Oxychilus inopinatus ( Uličný , 1887 ) is a species of small land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Oxychilidae , the glass snails .
Coregonus bavaricus , known as the kilch or Ammersee - Kilch in German , is a species of freshwater whitefish in the family Salmonidae .
Acacia loderi , known colloquially as nelia or nealie , is a species of Acacia native to Australia .
Aspilota vicina is a species of insect from the Braconidae family .
Balbaroo fangaroo is an extinct species of kangaroo .
Styrax crotonoides is a species of plant in the genus Styrax and family Styracaceae .
Polemonium californicum is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common names moving polemonium , low Jacob's - ladder , and California Jacob 's ladder .
Muntingia calabura , the sole species in the genus Muntingia , is a flowering plant native to southern Mexico , the Caribbean , Central America , and western South America south to Peru and Bolivia .
Trichomycterus balios is a species of pencil catfish endemic to Brazil , where it occurs in the upper portion of the Das Antas and Caí river basins ( Laguna dos Patos system ) , and the Mampituba river basin , in the state of Rio Grande do Sul .
Ceratophyllum submersum , commonly known as the soft hornwort , is a species of Ceratophyllum .
Mesoponera melanaria , is a species of ant of the subfamily Ponerinae .
Reimarochloa is a genus of New World plants in the grass family , native to North and South America including the Greater Antilles .
Tentoriceps is a monotypic genus of cutlassfish , family Trichiuridae , from the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
Rukwasuchus is an extinct genus of peirosaurid mesoeucrocodylian known from the middle Cretaceous Galula Formation of southwestern Tanzania .
Orthomegas maryae is a species of beetle in the Orthomegas genus that is in the Cerambycidae family .
Mellinus arvensis ( field digger wasp ) is a species of solitary wasp .
Salanoia is a genus of euplerid carnivoran with two currently described species found in Madagascar .
Eirenis barani , commonly known as Baran 's dwarf racer , is a species of snake in the Colubridae family .
Zabrus rotundicollis is a species of black coloured ground beetle in the Pelor subgenus that is can be found in Armenia , Iran and Turkey .
Lycium shawii , desert thorn or Arabian boxthorn is a species of thorny shrub adapted to desert environments .
Inanidrilus falcifer is a species of Annelid worm .
The Nuñez tree iguana , Liolaemus curis , is a species of lizard in the Iguanidae family .
Agrostophyllum philippinense is a species of orchid in the genus Agrostophyllum that was first described by Oakes Ames in 1910 .
Lentinula guarapiensis is a species of agaric fungus in the family Marasmiaceae that is found in Paraguay .
Bellator egretta , the streamer searobin , is a species of searobin native to the western Atlantic Ocean .
Cadlina pacifica is a species of sea slug or dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cadlinidae .
Bostrychus microphthalmus is a species of fish from the Eleotridae family .
It has only one species , Stylomecon heterophylla , the windpoppy , which is native to California and north western Mexico .
Nemegtosauridae is a family of probably titanosaurian sauropod dinosaurs based originally on two late Cretaceous Mongolian species known only from their diplodocid - like skulls :
Crinoids are marine animals that make up the class Crinoidea of the echinoderms ( phylum Echinodermata ) .
Rabidosa rabida also known as Rabid wolf spider , is a species of spiders from the Lycosidae family , which can be found from Maine to Florida and west to Texas in the United States .
Schistosomatidae is a family of digenetic trematodes with complex parasitic life cycles .
Turrisaspis elektor is an extinct species of groenlandaspid arthrodire placoderm .
Echinopsis candicans is a species of cactus from northern and western Argentina ( Monte Desert ) .
Texella cokendolpheri is a rare species of arachnid known by the common name Cokendolpher Cave harvestman .
Pachyphytum oviferum ( also named Sugaralmond plant or Moonstone ) is a species of the genus Pachyphytum in the family of Crassulaceae .
The only member of its genus , Allosmerus elongatus , the whitebait smelt , is an uncommon marine species of smelt , about which little is known .
Ormosia nobilis ( sometimes incorrectly : Ormosia novilis ) is a tree - forming plant species in the genus Ormosia .
Buddleja jinsixiaensis is a newly discovered species endemic to Shaanxi , China , where it grows in the Jinxia Grand Canyon at an elevation of c. 1,200 m. Two specimens were found , one in Quercus forest , another on a rocky slope , by a team led by Renbin Zhu in May , 2013 .
Hybodus ( `` humped tooth '' ) is an extinct genus of widespread and long - lived sharks , first appearing towards the end of the Permian period , and disappearing during the Late Cretaceous .
Trillium angustipetalum is a species of Trillium , plants which may be included within the lily family or the newer family Melanthiaceae .
Anopheles sinensis is a species of mosquito that transmits malaria as well as lymphatic filariasis .
Draba pterosperma is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name wingedseed draba .
Bellamya trochlearis is a species of large freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Viviparidae .
Orthotylus verticatus is a species of bug from a family of Miridae that can be found in France and Spain .
Diacamma ceylonense , also known as Sri Lanka queenless ant , is a species of ant of the subfamily Ponerinae .
Wasmannia is a genus of ants that are social , native to tropical habitats , and haplodiploid , with the reproductive castes ( queens and drones ) haploid , and the worker caste diploid .
Anopterus glandulosus , commonly known as native laurel or Tasmanian laurel , is a species of shrub or small tree in the family Escalloniaceae , endemic to the rainforests of western and southern Tasmania .
Eubacterium acidaminophilum is a Gram - positive bacterium species in the genus Eubacterium , notable for being an amino acid - degrading obligate anaerobe producing or utilizing H2 or formate .
Deiregyne is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae , native to Mexico , Guatemala and Honduras .
Lamprophis is a genus of medium - sized , nonvenomous snakes commonly referred to as African house snakes .
Cicurina baronia is a rare species of spider in the family Dictynidae known by the common name Robber Baron cave meshweaver .
Pharidae is a taxonomic family of saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs , currently classified in the unassigned Euheterodonta .
Sterculia apetala , commonly known as the Panama tree , camoruco or manduvi tree , is a species of plant in the Malvaceae family .
Hyla eximia , the mountain treefrog , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Mexico .
The Indian toad or ridged toad ( Bufo parietalis ) is a species of toad found in the Western Ghats of India .
In 2014 it was named and described by Jaime Headden and Hebert Bruno Nascimento Campos as a separate genus Banguela , with the type species Banguela oberlii .
Aratus pisonii , commonly known as the mangrove tree crab , is a species of crab which lives in mangrove trees in tropical and subtropical parts of the Americas , from Florida to Brazil on the Atlantic coast , and from Nicaragua to Peru on the Pacific coast .
Polygonum bidwelliae is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the knotweed family known by the common name Bidwell 's knotweed .
Agyneta gracilipes is a species of sheet weaver found in Cameroon , Gabon , Congo , Kenya and Angola .
Saurocytozoon is a genus of parasitic protozoa .
Vesperus brevicollis is a species of brown coloured western European beetle in the Vesperidae family that can be found in Portugal and Spain .
Dipetalogaster , a genus of Triatominae , the kissing bugs , has only a single species , Dipetalogaster maxima , which is found in the Mexican state of Baja California Sur .
The type species was named Obamadon gracilis after United States president Barack Obama , `` in reference to the tall , straight teeth , and the manner in which Mr. Obama has acted as a role model of good oral hygiene for the world . ''
Spiroplasma is a genus of Mollicutes , a group of small bacteria without cell walls .
Spinohybolasius spinicollis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Spinohybolasius .
Roeperocharis is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae , native to eastern Africa .
Acanthogammaridae is a family of amphipod crustaceans , endemic to Lake Baikal .
Phalaenopsis sumatrana is a species of orchid endemic to peninsular Thailand , Vietnam and southern Sumatra .
The Schneider 's shrub frog , ( Pseudophilautus schneideri ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family , endemic to Sri Lanka .
Acrostictomyia longistigma is a species of ulidiidae or picture - winged fly in the genus Acrostictomyia of the family Ulidiidae .
Carex atherodes is a species of sedge known by the common name wheat sedge .
Tropaeum ( `` Trophy '' ) is an extinct genus of ammonite cephalopod found throughout the oceans of the world during the Early Cretaceous .
Spirocodon is a monotypic genus of athecate hydroids and Spirocodon saltatrix is the only species in the genus .
Ophiopogon japonicus ( dwarf lilyturf , mondograss , fountainplant , monkeygrass ; Japanese : リュウノヒゲ ryu - no - hige ( `` dragon 's beard '' ) or ジャノヒゲ ja - no - hige ( `` snake 's beard '' ) ) is a species of Ophiopogon native to China , India , Japan , and Vietnam .
Buddleja suaveolens is endemic to central Chile , growing mostly in rocky areas along rivers at elevations of 500 -- 2,900 m. The species was first named and described by Kunth and Bouché in 1845 .
Baschkirites is an extinct cephalopod genus belonging to the ammonoid order Goniatitida that lived during the Early Carboniferous ( Bashkirian ) .
Plectritis ciliosa is a species of flowering plant in the honeysuckle family known by the common name longspur seablush .
Discohelicidae is an extinct family of sea snails with planispiral shells , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Vetigastropoda ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Haplomitrium andinum is a species of liverwort from Peru .
Arctostaphylos mewukka is a species of manzanita known by the common name Indian manzanita .
Atrophaneura semperi is a species of butterfly from the family Papilionidae that is found in Indonesia , Malaysia , and the Philippines .
Setosipennula is a genus of moth in the Pterophoridae family containing only one species , Setosipennula viettei , which is known from Madagascar .
The cavy family ( Caviidae ) is a family of rodents native to South America , including the domestic guinea pig , wild cavies , and the capybara , among other animals .
Phyllactinia guttata is a species of fungus in the Erysiphaceae family ; the anamorph of this species is Ovulariopsis moricola .
Belopus elongatus ( synonym of Centorus ( Belopus ) elongatus Herbst , 1797 ) is a species of darkling beetles in the subfamily Lagriinae .
Callomyia elegans is a fly species in the genus Callomyia found in Europe .
Phallostethus dunckeri is a species of fish in the Phallostethidae family .
Arrhenia acerosa , commonly known as the moss oysterling , is a species of agaric fungus in the family Hygrophoraceae .
Neptidopsis is a genus of nymphalid butterfly found in Africa , commonly called Sailors .
Psilocybe makarorae is a species of psilocybin mushroom in the family Strophariaceae .
Hipposideros grandis , the grand roundleaf bat ( also known as the grand leaf - nosed bat ) is a species of bat in the genus Hipposideros .
Ranunculus bonariensis is a species of buttercup known by the common name Carter 's buttercup .
Rhododendron farrerae ( Mrs. Farrer 's Rhododendron ) is a deciduous rhododendron species native to China ( Hong Kong , Hunan to Fujian ) , with violet flowers , reaching a height of 60 cm . ( 2 ft . ) .
Valvata macrostoma is a species of minute freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Valvatidae , the valve snails .
Euphorbia horrida ( African milk barrel ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Euphorbiaceae , native to South Africa .
Trichosporon mycotoxinivorans is a yeast species purportedly useful in the detoxification of various mycotoxins .
Aristea cantharophila is a plant species endemic to a small region of Western Cape Province , South Africa , Southeast of Cape Town .
Barbosania is an extinct genus of crestless ornithocheirid pterosaur from the Cretaceous Romualdo Member of the Santana Formation of Northeastern Brazil , dating to the Albian - Cenomanian stage .
The Palaeodictyoptera are an extinct order of medium - sized to very large , primitive Palaeozoic paleopterous insects .
Leptosphaeria is a genus of fungi in the family Phaeosphaeriaceae .
Ectomomyrmex astutus is a species of ant in the genus Ectomomyrmex .
Plectrurus aureus , commonly known as the Kerala burrowing snake , is a species of uropeltid snake endemic to India .
Subspecies Scopula rubiginata ochraceata is mostly treated as a species , Scopula ochraceata .
Gonatista major is a species of praying mantis native to the Caribbean and is found in Puerto Rico , on Hispaniola , and perhaps elsewhere .
Echinus esculentus , the European edible sea urchin or common sea urchin , is a species of marine invertebrate in the Echinidae family .
Ligumia nasuta ( eastern pondmussel ) is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Paralucia spinifera , commonly known as the Bathurst Copper or Purple Copper , is a species of butterfly in the Lycaenidae family .
Gallirallus is a genus that contains about a dozen living , and several recently extinct , species of rails that live in the Australasian - Pacific region .
Gebiidea is an infraorder of decapod crustaceans , formerly classified in the Thalassinidea .
Hyalella is a South and North American genus of mainly freshwater amphipods .
Scaphyglottis is a genus of orchids native to Mexico , Central America , northern South America and parts of the Caribbean .
Eosacantha is an extinct genus of tortoise beetle in the family Chrysomelidae and containing a single species Eosacantha delocranioides .
Bacillus sporothermodurans is a species of bacteria notable for producing highly heat - resistant endospores , hence its name .
Carabus perrini perrini is a subspecies of black - coloured beetle from Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to Ukraine .
Hugonia micans is a species of plant in the Linaceae family .
Abraliopsis falco is a species of enoploteuthid cephalopod found in the tropical waters of the East Pacific Ocean , and is known from Chile , Colombia , Costa Rica , Ecuador , El Salvador , Guatemala , México , Nicaragua , Panamá , Perú and the United States .
Speke 's gazelle ( Gazella spekei ) is the smallest of the gazelle species .
Ericameria nana is a North American species of flowering shrub in the daisy family known by the common names dwarf goldenbush and rubberweed .
Mertensophryne schmidti ( commonly known as Schmidt 's snouted frog ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Phallus drewesii is a species of stinkhorn mushroom endemic to São Tomé that was first described in 2009 .
Botrychium lunaria is a species of fern known by the common name moonwort or common moonwort .
