Quercus hypoxantha is a Mexican species of plant in the beech family .
Passandridae , the `` parasitic flat bark beetles , '' are a family of beetles notable for being one of the very few beetle families with larvae that are , as far as known , exclusively ectoparasitic on the immature stages of other beetles and Hymenoptera .
Phalacrognathus muelleri , colloquially the rainbow stag beetle , is a species of beetle in the family Lucanidae .
Thalassinidea is a former infraorder of decapod crustaceans that live in burrows in muddy bottoms of the world 's oceans .
The mydid fly genus Rhaphiomidas contains fewer than 30 species / subspecies , all of them occurring in the desert regions of the southwestern United States and adjacent portions of northwestern Mexico .
Urtica chamaedryoides , commonly called heartleaf nettle , is a species of flowering plant in the nettle family .
Plicofollis is a genus of sea catfishes found along the coasts of the Indian Ocean from Africa to Australasia with some species ranging up into the Philippines .
Sirenoscincus is a genus of burrowing lizards , skinks that are endemic to Madagascar .
Penstemon anguineus is a species of penstemon known by the common name Siskiyou beardtongue .
Xenotyphlops grandidieri is a species of blind snake endemic to Madagascar .
Aromobates saltuensis ( common name : salty rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
The Bucephaloidea are a superfamily of trematode flatworms , belonging to the large group Digenea .
Cortinarius argyrionus is a species of sequestrate ( truffle - like ) fungus in the family Cortinariaceae .
Betta tomi is a species of gourami native to the Malaysian Peninsula where it is currently only found in Johor .
Eriogonum palmerianum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Palmer 's buckwheat .
Stereocyclops ( common name : Brazilian dumpy frogs ) is a small genus of microhylid frogs endemic to the Atlantic forest of eastern Brazil .
Luzula lutea , is a species of perennial plant in Juncaceae family which is 12 - -15 centimetres ( 4.7 - -5.9 in ) tall .
Dichocoenia stellaris , commonly known as pancake star coral , is a species of stony coral in the family Meandrinidae .
Hesperostipa comata , commonly known as needle - and - thread grass , is a species of grass native to North America , especially the western third .
Plesiocystiscus josephinae is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Marginellidae , sometimes placed in the family Cystiscidae .
Trichostenidea rufopunctata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Trichostenidea .
The Oriental fire - bellied toad ( Bombina orientalis ) is a small ( 4 cm , 2 `` ) semiaquatic frog species found in Korea , northeastern China , and adjacent parts of Russia .
Lithobius microps ( also known as stone centipede ; or in the United States as Delcore 's Centipede ( It 's synonyms are Lithobius duboscqui and Sigibius puritanicus ) is a species of centipede from Lithobiidae family that can be found in the Northeast of the United States , England and South Wales .
Janetaescincus is a genus of burrowing skinks ( family Scincidae ) endemic to the Seychelles .
The Sepidiini is a tribe of ground - dwelling darkling beetles ( Tenebrionidae ) , that occurs across Africa , the Mediterranean Basin , the Arabian Peninsula and Mesopotamia .
Paracanthocobitis zonalternans also known as the Dwarf zipper loach is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Paracanthocobitis .
Gyrinus is a genus of small aquatic whirligig beetles in the family Gyrinidae native to the Palearctic ( including Europe ) , the Near East , the Nearctic and North Africa .
Campichoetidae is a small family of acalyptrate Diptera with only one genus Campichoeta Macquart , 1835.They are regarded by some authors as Diastatidae .
Pinus densata , commonly known as the Sikang pine , is a species of conifer in the Pinaceae family .
Calliophis is a genus of venomous elapid snakes , one of several known commonly as oriental coral snakes or Asian coral snakes .
Parablennius intermedius , the false Tasmanian blenny or horned blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the Indian ocean near Australian coasts .
Ceramaster patagonicus , the cookie star , is a species of sea star .
Pergularia is a genus of the botanical family Apocynaceae .
Conozoa is a genus of grasshoppers in the family Acrididae .
Pittosporum tobira is a species of flowering plant in the Pittosporum family known by several common names , including Japanese pittosporum , Japanese mock - orange and Japanese cheesewood .
Vitis arizonica , commonly known as Canyon grape , is a North American species of wild grape .
Mirabilis rotundifolia is a species of flowering plant in the four o'clock family known by the common name roundleaf four o'clock .
Caliciviridae is a family of viruses , members of Class IV of the Baltimore scheme .
Based on features of the peristome and recognition of a wrinkle layer , unique in this family , Frest et al . , 1981 , renamed the genus Sosioceras , in reference to its location , arguing for its separation .
Malus × micromalus ( also known as midget crabapple or Kaido crabapple ) , is a species in the genus Malus , in the family Rosaceae .
Swordfish are ectothermic animals ; however , along with some species of sharks , they have special organs next to their eyes to heat their eyes and brains .
Acontias is a genus of limbless skinks , the lance skinks , ( family Scincidae ) in the African subfamily Acontinae .
Phoeniculus is a genus of bird in the Phoeniculidae family .
Cyathea halconensis is a species of tree fern native to the islands of Luzon and Mindoro in the Philippines , where it grows in forest at an altitude of 1200 - 1700 m. The trunk of this plant is erect and 2 - 4 m tall .
Myrceugenia exsucca is an evergreen woody flowering plant species of the Myrtle family , Myrtaceae .
Opuntia polyacantha is a common species of cactus known by the common names plains pricklypear , hairspine cactus , panhandle pricklypear , and starvation pricklypear .
Although conventionally considered to be an order in the class Scyphozoa , recent genetic studies suggest that Stauromedusae should be elevated to a taxon equivalent of Scyphozoa and Cubozoa , and should therefore be known as the class Staurozoa .
Lactuca , commonly known as lettuce , is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae .
Cretaceogekko is an extinct monotypic genus of gecko ( represented by the type species Cretaceogekko burmae ) known from a single partial specimen preserved in amber from the Early Cretaceous of Burma .
Geranium arboreum is a rare species of geranium known by the common names Hawaiian red - flowered geranium and Hawaii red cranesbill .
Morania is a genus of cyanobacterium preserved as carbonaceous films in the Middle Cambrian Burgess Shale .
†Partula rustica was a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
Oman ypsilon , the Oman blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Indian ocean , around Oman .
Lonicera conjugialis is a species of honeysuckle known by the common name purpleflower honeysuckle .
Eupristocerus cogitans is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Eupristocerus .
Clausirion bicolor is a species of longhorn beetle in the family Cerambycidae .
Hemimenia is a genus of solenogasters , shell - less , worm - like mollusks .
The bacterial order Chlamydiales includes only obligately intracellular bacteria that have a chlamydia - like developmental cycle of replication and at least 80 % 16S rRNA or 23S rRNA gene sequence identity with other members of Chlamydiales .
Phyllachora is a genus of fungi in the family Phyllachoraceae .
Pygomeles is a genus of skinks endemic to Madagascar .
Fittonia verschaffeltii ( commonly known as Nerve Plant ) is a species of tropical plant native to Peru .
Donnie Ray Albert ( born January 10 , 1950 ) is an American operatic baritone who has had an active international career since 1976 .
Lauren Flanigan ( born May 18 , 1959 ) is an American operatic soprano who has had an active international career since the 1980s .
Nancy Fabiola Herrera is a Canarian mezzo - soprano opera singer .
Sandra Warfield ( June 8 , 1921 -- June 29 , 2009 ) was an American operatic mezzo - soprano who performed with New York City 's Metropolitan Opera from the 1950s through the 1970s .
Béatrice La Palme ( July 27 , 1878 -- January 8 , 1921 ) , was a soprano opera singer , violinist , and music teacher .
Robin Follman is an American operatic soprano who has appeared in many of the world 's best opera houses and concert halls in operas , oratorios , concerts , and recitals .
Isabella Girardeau ( née Calliari ? ; ? -- ? ) was an Italian operatic soprano who flourished in London , England from 1709 to 1712 .
Stephen Mahy is an Australian born tenor from Sydney , NSW best known for originating the role of Bob Gaudio in the Australian production of Jersey Boys .
Alessandro Bonci ( February 10 , 1870 -- August 10 , 1940 ) was an Italian lyric tenor known internationally for his association with the bel canto repertoire .
Andrew Foster - Williams ( born in Wigan , Greater Manchester ) is an English operatic bass - baritone , concert singer and recitalist .
Christa Mayer is a German operatic mezzo - soprano .
Irene Dalis ( born Yvonne Patricia Dalis , October 8 , 1925 -- December 14 , 2014 ) was an American mezzo - soprano singer , who had a long international career at the highest levels of world opera .
Denia Mazzola - Gavazzeni , is an operatic soprano , born 4 February 1953 in Bergamo , Italy .
Amy Evans ( 24 October 1884 -- 5 January 1983 ) was a Welsh soprano and actress known for her performances in oratorio , recitals , and opera .
Charles - Louis Sainte - Foy , born Charles - Louis Pubereaux , also known simply as Sainte - Foy ( 13 February 1817 -- 1 April 1877 ) was a French operatic tenor who sang at the Opéra - Comique for over 30 years .
Christian Kostal León de Castillo ( born 7 September 1985 ) is an Austrian - Mexican tenor , conceptual artist , musicologist and artistic director .
Nathan Berg ( born in Spalding , Saskatchewan , Canada ) is an operatic bass - baritone who has had a concert , opera and recording career largely in North America and Europe .
Birgit Nilsson ( 17 May 1918 -- 25 December 2005 ) was a celebrated Swedish dramatic soprano who specialized in operatic works of Wagner and Strauss , though she sang the operas of many other composers , including Verdi and Puccini .
Roland Hayes ( June 3 , 1887 -- January 1 , 1977 ) was an American lyric tenor and composer .
Marion Hood ( 1 April 1854 - 14 August 1912 ) was an English soprano who performed in opera and musical theatre in the last decades of the 19th century .
Barbara Smith Conrad ( born 1940 ) is an American operatic mezzo - soprano of international acclaim .
Jaume Aragall i Garriga ( Catalan pronunciation : ( ˈʒawmə əɾəˈɣaʎ ) ; born 6 June 1939 ) , better known as Giacomo Aragall , is a Spanish operatic tenor , considered one of the best ever , not just for the beauty of his voice but also for the wonderful way of singing and acting .
Orlandus Wilson ( 1917 -- December 30 , 1998 ) was one of the longest standing members of the Golden Gate Quartet and the group 's bass singer .
Mathilde Mallinger ( Croatian pronunciation : ( mǎliŋger ) ; 17 February 1847 -- 19 April 1920 ) was a famous Croatian lyric soprano opera singer .
Viola Gillette ( 1871 - 1956 ) , born Viola Pratt , was an American contralto from Salt Lake City .
Pauline Lucca ( April 25 , 1841 -- February 28 , 1908 ) was a prominent operatic soprano , born in the Austrian capital of Vienna .
Luigi Marini , ( 1885 -- 1942 ) was an Italian lyric tenor .
Lawrence Brownlee ( born 1972 ) is an American operatic tenor particularly associated with the bel canto repertoire .
André Pernet ( 1894 - -1966 ) was a French bass - baritone opera performer .
Deborah Polaski ( born May 26 , 1949 , in Richland Center , Wisconsin ) is an American opera and concert singer ( soprano ) .
McHenry Boatwright ( February 29 , 1928 -- November 5 , 1994 ) was an American operatic bass - baritone and singing teacher .
Lilli Lehmann , born Elisabeth Maria Lehmann , later Elisabeth Maria Lehmann - Kalisch ( 24 November 1848 , in Würzburg -- 17 May 1929 , in Berlin ) was a German operatic soprano of phenomenal versatility .
Giacinta Toso ( 1807 - 1889 ) , ( also Toso Puzzi or Puzzi Toso ) , Maman Puzzi , was an Italian operatic soprano who had a significant career in England during the 1820s and 1830s , before ill health forced her to retire from the stage .
Noemí Carrión Pérez , is a Spanish singer ( soprano and mezzo soprano ) , dancer , and actress , known also as Naymi and Noemí .
Dame Isobel Baillie , DBE ( 9 March 1895 -- 24 September 1983 ) was a Scottish soprano , popular in opera , oratorio and lieder .
Gemma Bellincioni ( Italian pronunciation : ( ˈdʒɛmma bellinˈtʃoːni ) ; 18 August 1864 -- 23 April 1950 ) was an Italian soprano and one of the best - known opera singers of the late 19th century .
Alenka Gotar is a Slovene soprano singer , born in Rodica pri Domžalah in 1977 .
Victoria Bezetti ( born 11 March 1937 ) is a Romanian classical soprano who had an active performance career from the 1960s through the 1990s .
Johan Reuter ( born 1969 in Copenhagen ) is a Danish baritone and opera singer .
Marietta Alboni ( 6 March 1826 -- 23 June 1894 ) was a renowned Italian contralto opera singer .
